    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a serious condition that develops before birth when a baby doesn't get enough iodine from their mother during pregnancy, leading to brain and nervous system damage. Iodine is an essential nutrient needed for the thyroid gland to work properly and for normal brain development, and without it, an infant can experience severe intellectual disability, speech problems, hearing loss, and poor growth. This condition is largely preventable in countries where iodized salt is available, but still occurs in areas where iodine intake is very low.",
