    "shortDesc": "Other specified hypothyroidism",
    "longDesc": "Other specified hypothyroidism",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes an underactive thyroid (hypothyroidism) caused by something other than the common causes like iodine deficiency or Hashimoto's disease. Your thyroid isn't producing enough hormones, which can slow your metabolism and cause symptoms like fatigue, weight gain, cold sensitivity, and dry skin—but the specific reason for it falls into a less typical or 'other' category that your doctor has identified.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and internal medicine doctors use this code when documenting thyroid conditions that don't fit standard hypothyroidism categories. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients being treated for thyroid hormone replacement therapy.",
