    "longDesc": "Nontoxic diffuse goiter",
    "plainEnglish": "Nontoxic diffuse goiter is an enlargement of your entire thyroid gland that is not causing an overactive thyroid (meaning your thyroid hormone levels are normal or you have an underactive thyroid). Your thyroid swells uniformly throughout, which can cause your neck to appear larger or feel full, and may lead to difficulty swallowing or breathing if the swelling becomes significant. This type of goiter is often caused by iodine deficiency, certain medications, or autoimmune conditions, but it's not producing excess thyroid hormone like toxic goiter would.",
