    "plainEnglish": "Acute thyroiditis is a sudden inflammation of your thyroid gland, which is the butterfly-shaped organ in your neck that controls your metabolism and energy levels. This inflammation can be caused by a viral or bacterial infection, and you might experience neck pain, swelling, fever, fatigue, and temporary changes in how your thyroid functions. The condition typically develops quickly over days to weeks and often improves on its own or with anti-inflammatory treatment.",
