    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a long-lasting inflammation of the thyroid gland that doesn't fit into the more common categories like Hashimoto's disease or Graves' disease. The inflammation can develop slowly over time and may affect how well your thyroid functions, potentially causing symptoms like fatigue, weight changes, or temperature sensitivity depending on whether your thyroid produces too much or too little hormone.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists and primary care physicians use this code when diagnosing chronic thyroid inflammation that has been present for an extended period. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing thyroid testing and evaluation for persistent thyroid dysfunction or antibody-related thyroid disease.",
