    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and general practitioners use this code when diagnosing uncommon or mixed thyroid disorders that don't meet criteria for hyperthyroidism, hypothyroidism, or other well-defined thyroid conditions. It may appear on patient EOB statements less frequently than common thyroid codes, typically only when a patient's specific thyroid condition is unusual or not yet fully classified.",
