    "plainEnglish": "This code means your doctor has identified a problem with your thyroid gland, but hasn't yet determined the specific type of thyroid disorder you have. Your thyroid is a butterfly-shaped gland in your neck that produces hormones controlling metabolism, energy, and body temperature, so when it's not working properly, you may experience symptoms like fatigue, weight changes, or temperature sensitivity. This unspecified diagnosis is typically temporary—your doctor will likely run blood tests to identify the exact condition (such as hypothyroidism, hyperthyroidism, or inflammation) so they can treat you properly.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, internists, and endocrinologists use this code when a thyroid disorder is suspected but not yet confirmed or classified. It commonly appears on EOBs as a preliminary diagnosis code while the patient awaits test results or specialist evaluation to pinpoint the exact thyroid condition.",
