    "longDesc": "Diabetes mellitus due to underlying condition with other diabetic arthropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "You have diabetes caused by another disease or condition your body has, and this diabetes is affecting your joints, causing pain, stiffness, or damage. This is different from type 1 or type 2 diabetes—your high blood sugar developed because of something else going on in your body (like cystic fibrosis, hemochromatosis, or pancreatitis), and as a result, your joints are experiencing diabetic-related complications. You may notice joint pain, swelling, or reduced mobility, particularly in your hands, feet, or other areas.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, rheumatologists, and primary care physicians use this code when managing patients whose diabetes stems from an underlying systemic disease and who also have joint complications. This code appears on EOBs for visits related to diabetes management and joint/arthropathy treatment, and is commonly documented in patients with conditions like hemochromatosis, pancreatitis, or cystic fibrosis-related diabetes.",
