    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a patient has diabetes caused by another medical condition (such as pancreatitis, cystic fibrosis, or hormonal disorders), and this diabetes has led to problems affecting the mouth or teeth—conditions like gum disease, tooth decay, mouth infections, or other oral tissue damage that developed as a result of the uncontrolled blood sugar. These oral complications occur because high blood sugar weakens the immune system and damages tissues, making the mouth more vulnerable to infection and decay.",
