    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and wound care specialists use this code when treating patients whose diabetes was triggered by medication or chemical exposure and who have developed a foot ulcer. It commonly appears on EOBs for patients on long-term steroid therapy or chemotherapy, and helps document the cause of diabetes for insurance and medical record purposes.",
