    "code": "E10.21",
    "rawCode": "E1021",
    "shortDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy",
    "longDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy means you have Type 1 diabetes (where your pancreas doesn't produce insulin) and it has begun to damage your kidneys. This kidney damage happens when consistently high blood sugar levels harm the small blood vessels in the kidneys that filter waste, which can eventually lead to kidney disease and difficulty removing waste from your body. You might experience swelling in your legs and feet, changes in urination patterns, or fatigue as your kidneys struggle to function properly.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists, and primary care doctors use this code when managing diabetic patients with kidney complications. It commonly appears on patient EOBs when someone with Type 1 diabetes has lab work or specialist visits related to kidney function monitoring or treatment of diabetic kidney disease.",
