    "plainEnglish": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic chronic kidney disease means your pancreas cannot make insulin (type 1 diabetes), and this condition has damaged your kidneys over time, reducing their ability to filter waste from your blood. Your kidneys are showing signs of permanent scarring or reduced function directly caused by years of high blood sugar, which is why your doctor is tracking this as a specific complication.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists, internists, and primary care physicians use this code when managing diabetic patients whose kidney function has declined due to diabetes. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements when billing for office visits, lab work (like kidney function tests), or specialist care related to managing both the diabetes and kidney disease.",
