    "shortDesc": "Type 1 diabetes w oth diabetic ophthalmic complication",
    "longDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with other diabetic ophthalmic complication",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates you have type 1 diabetes and an eye problem caused by the diabetes that isn't specifically cataracts, macular edema, or the most common diabetic retinopathy. This could include conditions like temporary vision changes from blood sugar fluctuations, diabetic macular swelling, or early signs of damage to the blood vessels in your eye. High blood sugar over time can harm the tiny blood vessels in your eyes, potentially affecting your vision if not managed.",
