    "shortDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy",
    "longDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 1 diabetes is an autoimmune condition where your pancreas stops making insulin, a hormone needed to control blood sugar. When high blood sugar levels persist over time, they can damage the nerves in your arms, legs, and feet—a condition called diabetic polyneuropathy—which causes numbness, tingling, burning sensations, or weakness, especially in the lower extremities. This code indicates you have both type 1 diabetes and this nerve damage complication.",
