    "plainEnglish": "Type 1 diabetes has damaged the nerves that control your body's automatic functions—like heart rate, digestion, blood pressure, and sweating—causing a condition called autonomic neuropathy. This happens when high blood sugar over time harms the small nerves that manage these involuntary bodily processes, and you might experience symptoms like dizziness when standing up, stomach problems, sexual dysfunction, or excessive or reduced sweating. This code indicates your diabetes has progressed to affect these deeper nerve systems, not just the nerves in your hands and feet.",
