    "shortDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus, presymptomatic, Stage 2",
    "longDesc": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus, presymptomatic, Stage 2",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 1 diabetes mellitus, presymptomatic, Stage 2 means your body's immune system is attacking the insulin-producing cells in your pancreas, but you don't have any symptoms yet. Stage 2 indicates that blood tests show clear evidence of this autoimmune destruction (you likely have multiple diabetes-related antibodies), putting you at very high risk of developing full diabetes within months or a few years. At this stage, you may feel completely normal, but your body is actively progressing toward a point where it won't be able to produce enough insulin on its own.",
