    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with hyperosmolarity with coma",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with hyperosmolarity with coma",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a life-threatening emergency where someone with type 2 diabetes has developed extremely high blood sugar levels that have caused their blood to become dangerously concentrated (hyperosmolar), leading to loss of consciousness. This condition, called hyperosmolar hyperglycemic state (HHS), happens when blood sugar climbs so high that it draws fluid out of cells, causing severe dehydration and confusion that can progress to a coma; it's a medical emergency requiring immediate hospitalization and intensive care.",
