    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy means you have type 2 diabetes (where your body can't properly use insulin to control blood sugar) and this has damaged your kidneys over time. High blood sugar levels gradually harm the tiny blood vessels in your kidneys that filter waste from your blood, leading to protein leaking into your urine and potentially reduced kidney function.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and nephrologists use this code when managing diabetic patients with kidney involvement. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with established diabetes seeking treatment for kidney complications, often triggering referrals to nephrology and requiring monitoring with lab work and kidney function tests.",
    "billable": true,
    "isNew": false,
    "isRevised": false,
    "chapterId": 4,
