    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus w oth diabetic kidney complication",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with other diabetic kidney complication",
    "plainEnglish": "You have type 2 diabetes that has caused damage to your kidneys beyond the most common complication (diabetic nephropathy). This could mean your kidneys are having trouble filtering waste properly, or you may be experiencing other kidney-related problems directly caused by your diabetes. Your doctor will need to monitor your kidney function closely and may adjust your diabetes management to prevent further kidney damage.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists, primary care physicians, and internists use this code when managing patients with type 2 diabetes who have developed kidney complications other than typical diabetic nephropathy. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving diabetes management and kidney function monitoring.",
