    "code": "E11.39",
    "rawCode": "E1139",
    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes w oth diabetic ophthalmic complication",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with other diabetic ophthalmic complication",
    "plainEnglish": "You have type 2 diabetes and a vision problem related to your diabetes that isn't one of the more common ones like diabetic retinopathy or cataracts. This could be several different eye conditions caused by high blood sugar over time, such as problems with the lens, nerve damage affecting eye movement, or swelling in parts of the eye. You may notice blurred vision, difficulty with eye focusing, or other visual changes, and you'll need eye care from your doctor to prevent further damage.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and ophthalmologists use this code when documenting diabetic eye complications during office visits or hospital care. It commonly appears on EOB statements when patients receive care for diabetes-related vision problems and helps insurance companies track complications related to diabetes management.",
