    "rawCode": "E1143",
    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes w diabetic autonomic (poly)neuropathy",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic autonomic (poly)neuropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes has damaged the nerves that control automatic functions in your body—like your heart rate, blood pressure, digestion, and bladder control—a condition called autonomic neuropathy. This happens when high blood sugar levels over time harm the delicate nerve fibers responsible for these vital automatic processes, potentially causing symptoms like dizziness when standing, constipation, difficulty digesting food, or problems with bladder or sexual function. This is a serious complication that requires ongoing diabetes management and monitoring to prevent further nerve damage.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and neurologists diagnose and manage this code, typically during comprehensive diabetes care visits or when patients report symptoms of autonomic dysfunction. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with longstanding Type 2 diabetes who require specialist evaluation and treatment planning for neuropathy complications.",
