    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic amyotrophy means you have type 2 diabetes that has caused nerve damage affecting the muscles in your hip and thigh area, leading to weakness and pain. This condition, called amyotrophy, occurs when high blood sugar damages the nerves that control these muscles, resulting in muscle wasting, difficulty walking, or sharp pain in the affected area. It's a complication that develops over time when diabetes isn't well-controlled.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, neurologists, and primary care physicians use this code when managing diabetic patients who develop this specific nerve-related muscle complication. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with documented diabetic neuropathy affecting skeletal muscles, typically following imaging, electrodiagnostic testing, or specialist evaluation.",
