    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic peripheral angiopathy without gangrene",
    "plainEnglish": "This code means you have type 2 diabetes that has damaged the blood vessels in your legs, feet, or other extremities, reducing blood flow to those areas. This condition, called diabetic peripheral angiopathy, can cause pain, numbness, weakness, or wounds that heal poorly in your affected limbs—but you do not currently have gangrene (tissue death). It develops over time when high blood sugar levels harm the walls of smaller arteries and blood vessels.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, cardiologists, and primary care physicians use this code when managing diabetic patients with documented vascular complications. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with long-standing type 2 diabetes who undergo vascular studies, imaging (like ultrasound or angiography), or specialized wound care evaluations.",
