    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with other circulatory complications means your blood sugar is not being controlled properly (type 2 diabetes), and this has caused problems with your blood circulation and blood vessels that don't fit into other specific categories. These circulation problems can affect blood flow to your heart, brain, limbs, or other organs, potentially leading to pain, numbness, slow wound healing, or in severe cases, tissue damage. Managing your blood sugar levels and working with your doctor to control blood pressure and cholesterol can help prevent these complications from worsening.",
