    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic neuropathic arthropathy means that you have type 2 diabetes, and the high blood sugar has damaged the nerves in your feet and legs (neuropathy), which in turn has caused damage to your joints. Because the nerve damage reduces your ability to feel pain and sense position, your joints—typically in the feet and ankles—can be repeatedly injured without you noticing, leading to progressive joint destruction and deformity (a condition called Charcot arthropathy). You may experience swelling, instability, unusual bone changes, or difficulty walking.",
