    "plainEnglish": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic dermatitis means you have type 2 diabetes that has caused a skin inflammation or infection. When blood sugar stays too high for extended periods, it damages the skin's ability to heal and protect itself, leading to redness, irritation, swelling, or infection that may itch or be painful. This skin problem is a direct complication of your diabetes, not just a coincidence.",
