    "plainEnglish": "You have type 2 diabetes (a condition where your body doesn't use insulin properly to control blood sugar) and you also have gum disease, which involves infection and inflammation of the tissues that hold your teeth in place. People with diabetes are more prone to gum disease because high blood sugar weakens the immune system and makes gum infections harder to fight, and gum disease in turn can make blood sugar control more difficult.",
