    "shortDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with unspecified complications",
    "longDesc": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with unspecified complications",
    "plainEnglish": "You have type 2 diabetes, which means your body has trouble using insulin to control blood sugar levels, and you're experiencing some complication from this condition that hasn't been specifically identified in your medical records. Type 2 diabetes develops when your body becomes resistant to insulin or doesn't make enough of it, and when left uncontrolled, it can cause various problems affecting your heart, kidneys, eyes, nerves, or other organs. This code is used when your doctor knows you have a diabetes-related complication but hasn't yet determined exactly which one it is—further testing or evaluation may be needed to pinpoint the specific issue.",
