    "code": "E13.01",
    "rawCode": "E1301",
    "shortDesc": "Oth diabetes mellitus with hyperosmolarity with coma",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with hyperosmolarity with coma",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a serious, life-threatening condition where a person with a less common type of diabetes develops extremely high blood sugar and dehydration so severe it causes loss of consciousness. The high concentration of glucose and other particles in the blood draws water out of cells, leading to severe dehydration and a dangerously altered mental state; this is a medical emergency requiring immediate hospitalization and intensive care.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, emergency medicine physicians, and intensivists use this code when treating patients with diabetic hyperosmolar hyperglycemic state (HHS) in a coma. While serious diabetic emergencies, this code rarely appears on routine EOB statements since patients are typically admitted to hospitals under inpatient emergency care rather than outpatient billing.",
