    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with ketoacidosis without coma",
    "plainEnglish": "You have a form of diabetes (other than type 1 or type 2) that has developed a serious metabolic emergency called ketoacidosis, where your blood becomes too acidic due to a buildup of ketones—chemicals produced when your body breaks down fat too quickly. You're experiencing this dangerous condition without being unconscious, but it requires immediate medical attention because left untreated, ketoacidosis can lead to coma and organ damage.",
