    "rawCode": "E1311",
    "shortDesc": "Oth diabetes mellitus with ketoacidosis with coma",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with ketoacidosis with coma",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a type of diabetes (not type 1 or type 2) that has developed a serious complication called ketoacidosis, where your blood becomes dangerously acidic because your body is breaking down fat too quickly for energy. You are currently in a coma (unconscious state) as a result of this life-threatening condition, which requires immediate emergency treatment to restore your body's chemical balance and lower your blood sugar.",
    "whoUses": "Emergency medicine physicians, intensivists, and endocrinologists use this code when treating patients in critical condition in the ER or ICU. This code appears on EOB statements for hospital admissions involving life-threatening diabetic emergencies, not routine outpatient care.",
