    "shortDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates you have a type of diabetes (not type 1 or type 2) that is causing damage to your kidneys, a condition called diabetic nephropathy. High blood sugar levels from uncontrolled diabetes can harm the small blood vessels in your kidneys over time, affecting their ability to filter waste from your blood properly. You may experience swelling in your legs or feet, high blood pressure, or changes in kidney function that your doctor monitors with blood and urine tests.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists (kidney specialists), and primary care physicians use this code when managing diabetic patients with kidney complications. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving dialysis, kidney function monitoring, or treatment for diabetic kidney disease.",
