    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that you have a form of diabetes (not type 1 or type 2) that has caused damage to your kidneys over time. Your kidneys are having trouble filtering waste from your blood properly because of your diabetes, which is a serious complication that requires ongoing monitoring and treatment to prevent further decline in kidney function.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists, primary care physicians, and internists use this code when managing patients with non-type 1/type 2 diabetes who have developed diabetic kidney disease. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with chronic kidney disease attributed to diabetes, particularly during dialysis, nephrology visits, or when monitoring kidney function.",
