    "rawCode": "E1336",
    "shortDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic cataract",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic cataract",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a patient has a less common type of diabetes (not Type 1 or Type 2) and has developed a cataract—a clouding of the eye's lens—as a direct complication of that diabetes. Over time, high blood sugar levels can damage the proteins in the lens, causing it to become progressively cloudier and affecting vision. This condition may eventually require cataract surgery to restore clear vision.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, and ophthalmologists use this code when documenting diabetes-related eye complications. It commonly appears on patient EOBs when billing for cataract evaluations, monitoring, or surgical procedures in diabetic patients with less common forms of diabetes.",
