    "rawCode": "E1342",
    "shortDesc": "Oth diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic polyneuropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that you have a form of diabetes (other than type 1, type 2, or gestational) that has caused nerve damage affecting multiple nerves throughout your body, a condition called polyneuropathy. This nerve damage typically develops gradually due to sustained high blood sugar levels and may cause symptoms like tingling, numbness, weakness, or pain—often starting in your feet and hands and potentially spreading upward if not managed.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, primary care physicians, neurologists, and podiatrists use this code when documenting diabetes-related nerve complications in patients with uncommon diabetes types (such as neonatal diabetes, drug-induced diabetes, or disease-associated diabetes). This code appears on EOB statements for patients whose diabetes management includes evaluation or treatment of nerve damage complications.",
