    "rawCode": "E1343",
    "shortDesc": "Oth diabetes mellitus w diabetic autonomic (poly)neuropathy",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic autonomic (poly)neuropathy",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a type of diabetes (not type 1 or type 2) that has caused damage to the nerves that control your automatic body functions—like heart rate, digestion, blood pressure, and sweating. Autonomic neuropathy means the nerve damage affects involuntary processes you don't consciously control, which can lead to symptoms like dizziness, digestive problems, difficulty regulating body temperature, or sexual dysfunction. This is a serious complication of diabetes that develops when high blood sugar levels harm these specialized nerves over time.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, internists, and neurologists use this code when diagnosing and managing diabetic patients with autonomic nerve damage. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with diabetes who are receiving treatment for diabetic complications, and it's important for documenting the specific type of nerve damage for insurance billing and ongoing medical management.",
