    "shortDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic amyotrophy",
    "longDesc": "Other specified diabetes mellitus with diabetic amyotrophy",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a form of diabetes (not Type 1 or Type 2) that has caused amyotrophy, which is a condition where muscles in the shoulders, hips, and thighs weaken and waste away due to nerve damage from uncontrolled blood sugar. You might experience muscle pain, weakness, or difficulty with activities like climbing stairs or getting up from a chair. This complication develops when diabetes damages the nerves that control muscle function.",
