    "plainEnglish": "Nondiabetic hypoglycemic coma is a life-threatening state of unconsciousness caused by dangerously low blood sugar levels in people who do not have diabetes. This can happen from excessive alcohol use, severe liver disease, certain medications, or rarely, from an insulin-producing tumor, and results in the brain not getting enough glucose to function properly. A person in this state is unresponsive and requires immediate emergency medical treatment to restore blood sugar levels.",
