    "plainEnglish": "Pseudohypoparathyroidism is a rare genetic condition where your body doesn't respond properly to parathyroid hormone (PTH), even though your parathyroid glands are producing it normally. This resistance causes your calcium levels to drop and phosphorus levels to rise, leading to symptoms like muscle cramps, tingling in your hands and feet, and sometimes abnormal bone development. Patients with this condition often have distinctive physical features such as short stature, round face, and shortened bones in their hands and feet.",
