    "plainEnglish": "This code describes uncommon or less typical problems with your parathyroid glands—four small glands in your neck that control calcium levels in your blood. When doctors use this code, it means you have a parathyroid disorder that doesn't fit the standard categories (like overactive or underactive parathyroids), such as parathyroid inflammation, cysts, or other conditions affecting how these glands function. Depending on the specific problem, you might experience symptoms related to abnormal calcium levels, such as fatigue, muscle weakness, or bone pain.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, internal medicine doctors, and surgeons use this code when treating patients with unusual parathyroid conditions that require specialist evaluation. This code appears less frequently on patient EOBs than common parathyroid disorders, typically appearing after lab work or imaging reveals an atypical parathyroid problem requiring further investigation or specialized treatment.",
