    "code": "E22.0",
    "rawCode": "E220",
    "shortDesc": "Acromegaly and pituitary gigantism",
    "longDesc": "Acromegaly and pituitary gigantism",
    "plainEnglish": "Acromegaly is a condition where your pituitary gland (a small gland at the base of your brain) produces too much growth hormone, usually because of a benign tumor. This causes your hands, feet, face, and other body parts to gradually enlarge and thicken over time, along with symptoms like joint pain, fatigue, and sleep problems. Pituitary gigantism is essentially the same condition occurring in children before their growth plates close, resulting in excessive overall height and body size.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists commonly diagnose and treat acromegaly and pituitary gigantism, often working with neurosurgeons if tumor removal is needed. This code appears on EOB statements when patients receive imaging, hormone testing, surgical consultation, or ongoing management for this growth hormone disorder.",
