    "shortDesc": "Hyperprolactinemia",
    "longDesc": "Hyperprolactinemia",
    "plainEnglish": "Hyperprolactinemia means your body is producing too much prolactin, a hormone that normally triggers milk production in women and plays other roles in both men and women. This overproduction can happen due to a pituitary gland tumor, certain medications, or other hormonal issues, and it may cause symptoms like unwanted breast milk discharge, irregular or absent periods, decreased sex drive, or erectile dysfunction. The condition is treatable once the underlying cause is identified.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists and primary care physicians most commonly diagnose and manage hyperprolactinemia, sometimes in collaboration with neurologists or neurosurgeons if a pituitary tumor is present. This code appears on EOB statements when patients undergo hormone testing or receive treatment for prolactin-related symptoms.",
