    "plainEnglish": "Your pituitary gland (a small gland at the base of your brain that controls many hormones) is producing too much of one or more hormones, but it's not one of the more common conditions like excess growth hormone or prolactin. This overproduction can cause various symptoms depending on which hormone is elevated, such as changes in metabolism, mood, or physical characteristics. The exact cause and symptoms depend on which specific hormone your pituitary is making too much of.",
