    "plainEnglish": "Your pituitary gland (a small gland at the base of your brain that controls many hormones) is producing too much of one or more hormones, but the specific hormone or cause hasn't been identified. This overproduction can lead to various symptoms depending on which hormones are affected, such as excessive growth, water retention, mood changes, or metabolic problems. Your doctor will need to do additional testing to figure out exactly which hormone is elevated and what's causing the problem.",
