    "shortDesc": "Conn's syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Conn's syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Conn's syndrome is a rare hormonal disorder where one or both adrenal glands (small glands that sit on top of your kidneys) produce too much of a hormone called aldosterone. This excess aldosterone causes your kidneys to retain sodium and lose potassium, leading to high blood pressure, weakness, muscle cramps, and sometimes abnormal heart rhythms. Most commonly, a benign tumor in one adrenal gland is responsible, though sometimes both glands are overactive without a tumor.",
