    "longDesc": "Glucocorticoid-remediable aldosteronism",
    "plainEnglish": "Glucocorticoid-remediable aldosteronism is a rare inherited condition where your adrenal glands produce too much of a hormone called aldosterone, which causes your body to retain salt and lose potassium, leading to high blood pressure and muscle weakness. Unlike typical high blood pressure, this form can actually be controlled or even reversed by taking glucocorticoid medications (like prednisone) rather than the usual blood pressure drugs. The condition is caused by an abnormal gene that gets passed down through families and typically appears at a young age.",
