    "plainEnglish": "An Addisonian crisis is a life-threatening emergency where your body suddenly stops producing enough of critical hormones called cortisol and aldosterone, which normally help regulate blood pressure, blood sugar, and your body's response to stress. This condition typically occurs in people with Addison's disease (a rare autoimmune condition affecting the adrenal glands) and causes symptoms like severe weakness, dangerously low blood pressure, confusion, and shock that require immediate emergency medical care.",
