    "longDesc": "Autoimmune polyglandular failure",
    "plainEnglish": "Autoimmune polyglandular failure means your immune system is attacking multiple hormone-producing glands in your body at the same time, causing them to stop working properly. This can affect your thyroid, pancreas, adrenal glands, and other endocrine organs, leading to a variety of symptoms like fatigue, weight changes, blood sugar problems, and hormonal imbalances. Because multiple glands are involved, you may need to take multiple medications to replace the hormones your body can no longer produce on its own.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists and internal medicine physicians typically diagnose and manage this condition, often in consultation with immunologists. While it's a serious chronic condition, this code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving ongoing specialist care and hormone replacement therapy management.",
    "billable": true,
