    "code": "E31.1",
    "rawCode": "E311",
    "shortDesc": "Polyglandular hyperfunction",
    "longDesc": "Polyglandular hyperfunction",
    "plainEnglish": "Polyglandular hyperfunction means that multiple hormone-producing glands in your body are overactive and producing too much hormone at the same time. This can involve your thyroid, parathyroid, pituitary, adrenal glands, or pancreas working in overdrive, causing symptoms like rapid heartbeat, anxiety, weight loss, excessive sweating, or mood changes depending on which glands are affected. The condition is relatively rare but requires careful monitoring because the excess hormones can affect many body systems.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists typically diagnose and manage this condition, often after a patient presents with multiple hormone-related symptoms that don't fit a single gland disorder. You may see this code on an EOB if you've had comprehensive endocrine testing or received specialized endocrinology care; it's less common on routine medical claims but appears when patients need ongoing management of complex hormone imbalances.",
