    "plainEnglish": "Multiple endocrine neoplasia type I (MEN1) is an inherited genetic condition where a person develops tumors in multiple hormone-producing glands, most commonly the parathyroid glands, pancreas, and pituitary gland. These tumors can cause serious hormonal imbalances and health problems, such as high calcium levels, low blood sugar, or excess stomach acid. People with MEN1 are born with the gene mutation and have a 50% chance of passing it to their children.",
