    "longDesc": "Multiple endocrine neoplasia [MEN] type IIA",
    "plainEnglish": "Multiple endocrine neoplasia type IIA (MEN IIA) is an inherited genetic condition where a person develops tumors in multiple endocrine glands—most commonly the thyroid, adrenal glands, and parathyroid glands. These tumors can produce excess hormones that cause various health problems like high blood pressure, calcium imbalance, or thyroid cancer, and the condition tends to run in families because it's caused by a mutation in a specific gene. People with MEN IIA need lifelong monitoring and screening to catch and manage these tumors early.",
