    "plainEnglish": "Carcinoid heart syndrome is a rare heart condition caused by a carcinoid tumor (a slow-growing cancer often found in the intestines or lungs) that releases serotonin and other chemicals into the bloodstream, damaging the valves on the right side of your heart. This damage causes the heart valves to leak or become stiff, leading to symptoms like shortness of breath, fatigue, irregular heartbeat, and swelling in your legs and abdomen. The condition develops when carcinoid tumors have spread (metastasized) to the liver, allowing these toxic chemicals to reach and injure your heart.",
