    "code": "E34.09",
    "rawCode": "E3409",
    "shortDesc": "Other carcinoid syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Other carcinoid syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Carcinoid syndrome is a rare condition caused by neuroendocrine tumors (slow-growing hormone-producing cancers, usually in the digestive system) that release excessive amounts of chemicals like serotonin into the bloodstream. This code covers forms of carcinoid syndrome other than the most common type, and patients typically experience symptoms such as facial flushing, chronic diarrhea, abdominal pain, and sometimes heart valve problems. The symptoms occur because these excess chemicals affect blood vessels and other body tissues.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, gastroenterologists, and endocrinologists use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with neuroendocrine tumors and their associated hormonal effects. This code appears less frequently on EOB statements than common conditions, as carcinoid syndrome is relatively rare, but it will appear when a patient is being treated for symptoms or complications related to a diagnosed neuroendocrine tumor.",
