    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a condition where your intestines are producing too much of certain hormones that control digestion, metabolism, or other body functions. While your intestines normally release these hormones in measured amounts to help with digestion and nutrient absorption, in this case they're being released in excessive quantities, which can cause various symptoms like diarrhea, cramping, or metabolic changes depending on which specific hormone is overproduced.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists, endocrinologists, and internal medicine physicians use this code when evaluating patients with unexplained digestive symptoms, chronic diarrhea, or suspected hormone-related metabolic disorders. It typically appears in hospital records and specialist referral documentation rather than on routine patient EOB statements, as it usually represents a diagnostic finding during workup rather than a primary patient complaint.",
