    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means your body is producing a hormone in an abnormal location or in an abnormal way—not where it should be produced or in the amount it should be. For example, a lung tumor might produce thyroid hormone, or a pancreatic tumor might produce insulin-like substances when it shouldn't. This can cause various symptoms depending on which hormone is being produced and where it's coming from.",
