    "longDesc": "Short stature due to endocrine disorder, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Short stature due to endocrine disorder, unspecified means your child or you are unusually short because of a problem with one of the body's hormone-producing glands, but the exact gland or specific hormone disorder hasn't been identified yet. This could involve the pituitary gland, thyroid, or other endocrine organs that regulate growth, rather than being due to genetics, nutrition, or other non-hormonal causes. Further testing is typically needed to pinpoint which specific hormone imbalance is responsible.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, endocrinologists, and pediatric growth specialists use this code when evaluating children with delayed growth or short stature caused by hormonal issues. It commonly appears on EOB statements for children undergoing growth hormone evaluations, thyroid testing, or other endocrine workups before a more specific diagnosis is confirmed.",
