    "longDesc": "Constitutional short stature",
    "plainEnglish": "Constitutional short stature means you are significantly shorter than average for your age and sex, but this is due to your natural body makeup—not a disease or hormone problem. This is a normal variation in human growth where some people are genetically programmed to be shorter, and their growth and development patterns are otherwise completely healthy.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians and endocrinologists use this code when evaluating children with short stature to distinguish normal genetic variation from medical conditions requiring treatment. This code appears on EOBs for routine growth assessments and specialist consultations, though it's typically not associated with treatment claims since constitutional short stature itself doesn't require medical intervention.",
