    "shortDesc": "Primary insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1) deficiency",
    "longDesc": "Primary insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1) deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Your body is not producing enough IGF-1, a hormone that works alongside growth hormone to help you grow, build muscle, and develop properly. This is a rare condition where the problem originates in your body's own ability to make this hormone, rather than from a shortage of growth hormone itself. You might experience short stature, slow growth in childhood, weak muscles, or delayed development depending on the severity.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatric endocrinologists and growth specialists typically diagnose and manage this condition, though adult endocrinologists may also encounter it. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for children being evaluated for poor growth or growth hormone-related disorders.",
