    "shortDesc": "Insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1) resistance",
    "longDesc": "Insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1) resistance",
    "plainEnglish": "IGF-1 resistance means your body's cells don't respond properly to insulin-like growth factor-1, a natural hormone that helps control growth and metabolism. This can result in abnormal growth patterns, metabolic problems, or difficulty gaining/losing weight despite adequate nutrition. Your body produces the hormone normally, but the cells essentially \"ignore\" its signals, similar to insulin resistance in diabetes.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists primarily use this code when diagnosing growth disorders and metabolic abnormalities in pediatric and adult patients. It appears less frequently on patient EOBs than common codes, but may appear when patients undergo comprehensive endocrine workup or growth hormone studies.",
