    "shortDesc": "Other genetic causes of short stature",
    "longDesc": "Other genetic causes of short stature",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a patient has unusually short height caused by an inherited genetic condition that isn't one of the common well-known growth disorders. There are many different genetic mutations and hereditary patterns that can result in short stature, and this code is used when the specific genetic cause falls outside the more frequently diagnosed conditions like growth hormone deficiency or Turner syndrome. A patient with this diagnosis may have been evaluated by their doctor for slow growth or significantly shorter-than-average height, and genetic testing or family history helped identify that an inherited gene variation is responsible.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatric endocrinologists and geneticists primarily use this code when evaluating children with unexplained short stature and identifying rare genetic causes through testing. This code appears less frequently on patient EOB statements compared to more common growth disorders, but may be seen when insurance is processing claims for genetic testing, specialist consultations, or growth-related treatments after a genetic diagnosis has been confirmed.",
