    "plainEnglish": "This code is used when a patient has unusually short height due to a genetic factor, but the specific genetic cause hasn't been identified or pinpointed. Rather than a known genetic condition like Turner syndrome or growth hormone deficiency, this diagnosis means the doctors recognize that something in the patient's genes is limiting their growth, but they haven't determined exactly what that genetic factor is. Patients with this diagnosis may have had genetic testing or growth evaluations, but the results either didn't reveal a specific diagnosis or the cause remains unclear.",
