    "shortDesc": "Other short stature due to endocrine disorder",
    "longDesc": "Other short stature due to endocrine disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes abnormally short height caused by a problem with your hormones or endocrine glands—the system that produces and regulates hormones like growth hormone, thyroid hormone, or others that control body growth and development. Unlike genetic short stature (which runs in families), this type of short height is specifically the result of a medical condition affecting your endocrine system, such as growth hormone deficiency, thyroid disease, or other hormonal imbalances. A patient with this diagnosis would have been evaluated by their doctor to rule out other causes of short stature and to identify the specific hormone problem responsible.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatric endocrinologists and general pediatricians most commonly use this code when managing children with growth disorders linked to hormonal dysfunction. It may appear on EOB statements for children receiving growth hormone therapy, thyroid replacement, or other endocrine treatments, though it's more frequently seen in specialist billing and medical records than on routine patient statements.",
