    "plainEnglish": "Constitutional tall stature means you are naturally very tall due to your genes and normal body development, not because of a disease or hormonal imbalance. This is simply how your body is built—your bones and overall growth patterns are longer than average, but everything else about your health and hormone levels is working normally. You may see this code if your doctor has evaluated your height and confirmed there's no underlying medical condition causing it.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists and pediatricians typically use this code when evaluating children or adolescents with excessive height to rule out growth hormone disorders or other metabolic conditions. This code rarely appears on patient EOB statements since constitutional tall stature is a normal variation rather than a disorder requiring treatment, though it may be documented during diagnostic workup for other height-related concerns.",
