    "shortDesc": "Androgen insensitivity syndrome, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Androgen insensitivity syndrome, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Androgen insensitivity syndrome (AIS) is a condition where a person's body doesn't respond properly to male hormones called androgens, even though those hormones are present. This happens because of a genetic difference that affects how cells receive and use androgen signals, which can impact sexual development, reproductive function, and other body processes. Depending on the severity, people with this condition may experience differences in genital development, infertility, or other physical variations.",
