    "plainEnglish": "Complete androgen insensitivity syndrome (CAIS) is a condition where a person's body cells cannot respond to male hormones (androgens) like testosterone, even though the hormones are present in normal amounts. This occurs due to a genetic mutation affecting how cells receive and process these hormones. People with CAIS typically have female external genitalia and internal reproductive structures, but may have undescended testes and infertility, and the condition is usually discovered during evaluation for primary amenorrhea (lack of menstruation) or infertility.",
