    "plainEnglish": "Partial androgen insensitivity syndrome (PAIS) is a condition where the body's cells don't respond fully to male hormones (androgens) like testosterone, even though the hormones are present. This happens because of a defect in the androgen receptor protein that allows cells to 'hear' and respond to these hormones. People with PAIS may have a mix of male and female characteristics, and the specific effects depend on how much the body can respond to these hormones, potentially affecting genital development, fertility, and secondary sex characteristics.",
