    "longDesc": "Other intraoperative complications of endocrine system",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes an unexpected problem that occurred during surgery involving your endocrine system (the glands that produce hormones like your thyroid, pancreas, or adrenal glands). These complications could include things like accidental damage to the gland, excessive bleeding, or other unforeseen difficulties that happened while the surgeon was operating. You would typically only see this code if something went wrong during your procedure that was directly related to the gland or organ being treated.",
    "whoUses": "Surgeons (especially endocrine surgeons), general surgeons, and anesthesiologists use this code when documenting operative complications. It appears less frequently on patient EOBs since it's mainly an administrative code for medical record-keeping; patients would more likely see it if they received a detailed operative report or faced additional billing related to managing the intraoperative problem.",
