    "code": "E42",
    "rawCode": "E42",
    "shortDesc": "Marasmic kwashiorkor",
    "longDesc": "Marasmic kwashiorkor",
    "plainEnglish": "Marasmic kwashiorkor is a severe form of protein-energy malnutrition that combines symptoms of both marasmus (extreme wasting and weight loss from overall calorie starvation) and kwashiorkor (protein deficiency causing fluid retention and swelling). This life-threatening condition typically occurs in infants and young children in areas with severe food scarcity or inadequate nutrition, and patients present with muscle wasting, weakness, edema (swelling), and often organ dysfunction.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, nutritionists, emergency medicine physicians, and international health/humanitarian organizations diagnose and treat this code, primarily in resource-limited settings or among severely malnourished populations. It rarely appears on typical patient EOB statements in developed countries but is commonly documented in cases involving child abuse with severe neglect or in medical missions to developing nations.",
