    "shortDesc": "Unspecified severe protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "longDesc": "Unspecified severe protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "plainEnglish": "This code means your body is severely malnourished—you're not getting enough calories and protein from food to meet your basic nutritional needs. This can happen due to poverty, inability to eat, severe illness, or lack of access to food, and it can cause weakness, weight loss, muscle wasting, and impaired healing. Severe malnutrition like this can affect how well your body fights infections and recovers from illness.",
    "whoUses": "Hospitalists, primary care physicians, gastroenterologists, and nutritionists use this code when caring for severely malnourished patients in hospital or outpatient settings. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving nutritional support, hospitalization, or treatment for conditions causing severe food insecurity or inability to eat.",
