    "shortDesc": "Moderate protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "longDesc": "Moderate protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "plainEnglish": "Moderate protein-calorie malnutrition means your body isn't getting enough calories and protein from food to function properly, and the deficiency has reached a moderate level of severity. This can happen due to poor diet, difficulty swallowing or eating, certain illnesses, or lack of access to adequate food. You might experience weight loss, muscle weakness, fatigue, or slow wound healing.",
    "whoUses": "This code is commonly used by primary care physicians, hospitalists, registered dietitians, and specialists treating malnourished patients in hospitals, nursing homes, or outpatient settings. It frequently appears on EOB statements for patients receiving nutritional counseling, supplemental feeding, or hospital care where malnutrition is documented as part of their diagnosis.",
