    "shortDesc": "Mild protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "longDesc": "Mild protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "plainEnglish": "Mild protein-calorie malnutrition means your body isn't getting enough protein and calories from food to meet its basic needs, but the deficiency is not severe. This can happen when someone isn't eating enough overall, has limited access to food, or has a condition that prevents proper nutrition—and it may cause fatigue, weakness, or slow wound healing. Unlike more serious malnutrition, mild protein-calorie malnutrition can often be improved by increasing food intake or ensuring better nutrition.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, dietitians, geriatricians, and hospitalists use this code when treating patients with inadequate nutrition, particularly in elderly patients, those with chronic illnesses, or individuals recovering from surgery or illness. It appears on EOB statements when nutritional assessment and counseling are provided during office visits or hospital stays, and is increasingly common in documentation for patients at risk of poor outcomes due to undernutrition.",
