    "longDesc": "Retarded development following protein-calorie malnutrition",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes stunted growth and delayed development in children who have not received adequate nutrition, particularly enough protein and calories. When a child doesn't eat enough food or gets insufficient protein over an extended period, their body cannot grow properly or develop at a normal pace, which can affect their height, weight, and mental development. This condition is most commonly seen in parts of the world with food scarcity, extreme poverty, or in cases of severe neglect or eating disorders.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, family medicine doctors, and nutritionists use this code when evaluating children with signs of malnutrition-related growth failure and developmental delays. It appears in clinical settings focused on child health, malnutrition management, and international/public health contexts, and may occasionally appear on EOB statements for children receiving treatment for severe nutritional deficiencies.",
