    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means your body is not getting enough overall nutrition—specifically, you're not consuming adequate protein and calories to meet your body's basic needs. This can happen due to poverty, food scarcity, difficulty eating, severe illness, or poor diet, and it may cause weakness, weight loss, muscle wasting, fatigue, and a weakened immune system that makes you more prone to infections.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care doctors, hospitalists, nutritionists, and social workers commonly use this code when a patient presents with signs of severe malnutrition but the specific type hasn't been identified yet. It frequently appears on EOB statements for hospital admissions, emergency department visits, and follow-up care, and often triggers referrals to nutrition support or social services.",
