    "plainEnglish": "Dry beriberi is a serious nutritional disease caused by severe vitamin B1 (thiamine) deficiency that damages your nerves and muscles, leading to weakness, numbness, tingling sensations, and difficulty walking. This condition typically develops in people with extremely poor nutrition, chronic alcoholism, or certain medical conditions that prevent proper absorption of this essential vitamin. Without treatment to restore vitamin B1 levels, the nerve damage can become permanent and progressively worsen.",
