    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, nutritionists, and gastroenterologists use this code when diagnosing zinc deficiency, particularly in patients with malnutrition, malabsorption disorders, or restrictive diets. It may appear on EOB statements when a patient receives nutritional assessment or supplementation treatment, though it's more commonly seen in inpatient or specialist settings rather than routine primary care billing.",
