    "longDesc": "Magnesium deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Magnesium deficiency means your body doesn't have enough magnesium, a mineral that's essential for muscle function, nerve signaling, heart rhythm, and bone health. This can happen due to poor diet, certain medications (like diuretics), digestive problems, or increased loss through sweat or urine, and you may experience muscle weakness, cramps, fatigue, or irregular heartbeats.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, nephrologists, and gastroenterologists commonly use this code when patients present with symptoms of low magnesium or when lab tests confirm deficiency. It appears on EOB statements when magnesium supplementation or treatment is ordered, though it's relatively uncommon compared to other nutrient deficiencies.",
