    "plainEnglish": "Chromium deficiency means your body doesn't have enough chromium, a mineral that helps regulate blood sugar levels and supports metabolism. This condition is rare in the general population but can occur in people receiving long-term intravenous feeding without adequate chromium supplementation, or occasionally from severe malnutrition. Symptoms may include impaired glucose control, elevated blood sugar, and neurological changes.",
    "whoUses": "Registered Dietitians, Internal Medicine physicians, and specialists in nutrition medicine use this code, particularly when managing patients on parenteral nutrition (IV feeding) or investigating nutritional deficiencies. It appears less frequently on patient EOBs unless the patient is hospitalized or receiving specialized nutritional support, as routine screening for chromium deficiency is uncommon in outpatient settings.",
