    "plainEnglish": "Vanadium deficiency means your body doesn't have enough vanadium, a trace mineral that plays a role in bone health, metabolism, and other body functions. This condition is extremely rare in people eating a normal diet, as vanadium is found in many foods like grains, vegetables, and seafood. You might experience symptoms related to bone weakness or metabolic issues, though deficiency is so uncommon that it's mainly seen in people on long-term artificial nutrition without adequate mineral supplementation.",
