    "rawCode": "E643",
    "shortDesc": "Sequelae of rickets",
    "longDesc": "Sequelae of rickets",
    "plainEnglish": "Rickets is a disease that softens bones in children, usually caused by vitamin D deficiency, and this code identifies the lasting effects that remain after the rickets has healed. Once rickets resolves, it can leave permanent bone deformities, stunted growth, or weakened bones that may cause ongoing problems. Someone with this diagnosis had rickets earlier in life and is now dealing with the long-term consequences, such as bent legs, short stature, or brittle bones that didn't develop properly.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, orthopedic surgeons, and endocrinologists use this code when evaluating children or young adults with permanent bone changes from past rickets. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving ongoing care for bone deformities, physical therapy, or orthopedic interventions related to their previous rickets.",
