    "plainEnglish": "This code describes lasting health problems that resulted from nutritional deficiencies in the past—such as not getting enough vitamins, minerals, or other essential nutrients. Even though the original nutritional problem may have been resolved, your body is still experiencing long-term effects or complications from that deficiency. For example, this might include weakness, bone problems, vision issues, or other organ damage that developed because of insufficient nutrition at some point.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, nutritionists, internists, and gastroenterologists use this code when treating patients with residual health effects from past malnutrition or vitamin/mineral deficiencies. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients seeking treatment related to lingering complications from nutritional problems, particularly in cases of chronic malabsorption, eating disorders, or severe past undernutrition.",
