    "shortDesc": "Sequelae of unspecified nutritional deficiency",
    "longDesc": "Sequelae of unspecified nutritional deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes long-term health problems that resulted from a nutritional deficiency in the past, but the specific nutrient that was lacking is not documented in your medical records. Nutritional deficiencies occur when your body doesn't get enough of essential vitamins, minerals, or other nutrients, and this code is used when those past deficiencies have caused lasting effects on your health that continue today—such as muscle weakness, bone problems, or other complications—even though the original deficiency may have been treated.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care doctors, internists, and registered dietitians use this code when treating patients with long-standing complications from malnutrition or nutritional deficiencies. It commonly appears on medical records in hospitals and outpatient clinics but is less frequently seen on patient EOB statements unless it's the primary reason for a treatment visit; more often it serves as a secondary diagnosis code supporting why a patient needs ongoing care.",
