    "shortDesc": "Localized adiposity",
    "longDesc": "Localized adiposity",
    "plainEnglish": "Localized adiposity means you have an abnormal buildup of fat in a specific area of your body, rather than being overweight overall. This could appear as a fatty lump or deposit under the skin in one particular spot, such as on the neck, shoulders, abdomen, or other body areas. While it's not dangerous by itself, it may be a cosmetic concern or sometimes develop as part of certain metabolic conditions.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, dermatologists, and endocrinologists use this code when documenting localized fat deposits that don't fit the pattern of general obesity. It appears on EOB statements less frequently than general obesity codes, typically when the abnormal fat distribution is the specific reason for the visit or is being monitored as part of metabolic evaluation.",
