    "longDesc": "Morbid (severe) obesity due to excess calories",
    "plainEnglish": "This code means you have severe obesity that has developed because you've been consuming more calories than your body uses over a long period of time. Unlike some weight conditions that may be related to hormonal or genetic factors, this diagnosis specifically indicates that the excess weight is primarily the result of taking in too many calories through food and drink. You may experience health complications related to carrying significantly excess weight, such as joint stress, breathing difficulties, or increased risk of chronic diseases.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, endocrinologists, and bariatric surgeons use this code when evaluating and treating patients with severe obesity. It commonly appears on EOB statements because insurance companies often require this specific code to determine coverage for weight-management treatments, medications, or bariatric surgery, as well as to track obesity-related health risks.",
