    "rawCode": "E66813",
    "shortDesc": "Obesity, class 3",
    "longDesc": "Obesity, class 3",
    "plainEnglish": "Class 3 obesity means your body mass index (BMI) is 40 or higher, which is considered severe obesity and poses significant health risks. This level of excess weight increases your risk of serious conditions like heart disease, diabetes, sleep apnea, and joint problems, and typically requires medical intervention such as lifestyle changes, medications, or in some cases bariatric surgery.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, endocrinologists, bariatric surgeons, and weight management specialists use this code to document and track severe obesity during treatment planning. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements and is often used to justify insurance coverage for weight loss treatments, medications, or surgery.",
