    "plainEnglish": "This code is used when you have obesity (excess body fat and weight) that doesn't fit into the main categories doctors typically track, such as obesity related to a specific complication or a rare underlying cause. It's a catch-all code for people who are overweight but whose situation is unusual or complex enough that a more specific obesity diagnosis doesn't apply. You might see this if you have obesity along with an uncommon medical condition or if your doctor needs to document your weight-related health concern in a non-standard way.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, internists, and obesity medicine specialists use this code when documenting weight-related conditions that don't fit standard categories. It appears on EOB statements when insurance companies need to track obesity-related visits or treatments, though it's less common than other obesity codes and may not always trigger specific coverage determinations.",
