    "rawCode": "E672",
    "shortDesc": "Megavitamin-B6 syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Megavitamin-B6 syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Megavitamin-B6 syndrome is a toxic condition that develops when someone takes extremely high doses of vitamin B6 (pyridoxine) supplements over an extended period. This excess intake can damage nerves, causing symptoms like numbness, tingling, and loss of coordination, typically in the hands and feet. The condition is reversible if the excessive vitamin supplementation is stopped, but continued high-dose use can lead to permanent nerve damage.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists and primary care physicians typically diagnose and manage this condition, often uncovered during evaluation of unexplained neuropathy or numbness. This code appears rarely on patient EOBs, as it's most commonly documented in hospital or specialty clinic settings when patients present with nerve damage symptoms and disclose high-dose B6 supplementation use.",
