    "plainEnglish": "This code describes long-term complications that have developed after receiving excessive nutritional support, typically from prolonged intravenous feeding or over-nutrition. When the body receives too many calories or nutrients for an extended period—often during intensive medical treatment or recovery—it can lead to lasting problems such as metabolic imbalances, organ damage, or nutritional abnormalities that persist even after the excess nutrition has stopped.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists, intensivists, hospitalists, and nutritionists use this code when treating patients with long-term effects from prior aggressive nutritional support, particularly in cases of prolonged ICU care or post-surgical recovery. It appears less commonly on patient EOBs since it typically applies to complications identified during ongoing medical management rather than as a primary acute diagnosis.",
