    "code": "E70.0",
    "rawCode": "E700",
    "shortDesc": "Classical phenylketonuria",
    "longDesc": "Classical phenylketonuria",
    "plainEnglish": "Classical phenylketonuria (PKU) is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down an amino acid called phenylalanine, which is found in many protein-containing foods. Because phenylalanine builds up in the blood and brain, it can cause serious damage to brain development and function, leading to intellectual disability, light skin pigmentation, a musty or mouse-like body odor, and seizures if left untreated. The good news is that when detected early through newborn screening (which is standard in most developed countries), a strict low-phenylalanine diet can prevent these complications and allow people with PKU to live normal, healthy lives.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, metabolic disorder specialists, and genetic counselors primarily use this code when diagnosing PKU in newborns or young children. This code appears on EOB statements when families have genetic testing, metabolic screening, or ongoing management visits for their child's PKU care.",
