    "rawCode": "E701",
    "shortDesc": "Other hyperphenylalaninemias",
    "longDesc": "Other hyperphenylalaninemias",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes elevated levels of phenylalanine (an amino acid) in the blood that are not caused by phenylketonuria (PKU), the most common form of this condition. These other forms of hyperphenylalaninemia can result from defects in the enzymes that break down phenylalanine or from problems with cofactors needed for proper metabolism. Patients may have mild to moderate elevations in blood phenylalanine levels and may experience developmental delays, intellectual disability, or light-colored skin, hair, and eyes if untreated, though symptoms are typically less severe than with classic PKU.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic disease specialists, pediatricians, and genetic counselors use this code when evaluating patients (usually identified through newborn screening) with elevated phenylalanine that doesn't fit the classic PKU diagnosis. It appears on EOB statements when patients require specialized metabolic testing, genetic counseling, or management for these rare amino acid disorders.",
