    "plainEnglish": "Your body normally breaks down an amino acid called tyrosine, which comes from protein in your diet and is used to make important chemicals like dopamine and thyroid hormones. This code means there's a problem with how your body processes tyrosine, but the specific type of disorder hasn't been identified or documented yet. Depending on the severity, this could affect energy levels, mood, skin pigmentation, or thyroid function, though many people with mild tyrosine metabolism issues have no noticeable symptoms.",
