    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to rare metabolic disorders that affect how your body processes tyrosine, an amino acid (building block of protein) that your body normally uses to make important substances like neurotransmitters and thyroid hormones. When tyrosine metabolism goes wrong in ways other than the more common conditions, it can lead to a buildup of tyrosine or related chemicals in the blood or urine, potentially causing developmental delays, intellectual disability, or other health problems depending on the specific disorder. These are typically inherited genetic conditions that are detected through newborn screening or genetic testing.",
