    "shortDesc": "X-linked ocular albinism",
    "longDesc": "X-linked ocular albinism",
    "plainEnglish": "X-linked ocular albinism is a rare inherited condition affecting eye pigmentation that is passed down through genes and primarily affects males. People with this condition have reduced pigment in the eye structures, particularly the retina and iris, which causes vision problems such as reduced visual sharpness, sensitivity to light, and sometimes involuntary eye movements. The condition is \"ocular\" because it mainly affects the eyes, unlike other forms of albinism that affect skin and hair color throughout the body.",
    "whoUses": "Ophthalmologists and geneticists primarily diagnose and manage this condition, often identified in childhood when vision problems or eye movement abnormalities are noticed. This code appears less frequently on patient EOBs compared to more common eye conditions, but may be seen when insurance covers genetic testing, eye exams, or vision correction treatments for this inherited disorder.",
