    "plainEnglish": "Chediak-Higashi syndrome is a rare inherited immune disorder where your white blood cells don't work properly because they contain abnormal structures called granules. This means your body has trouble fighting off infections and may experience recurrent bacterial or viral infections, along with other complications affecting blood cells and organ function. People with this condition may also notice pale skin and hair (because the same genetic defect affects pigment cells) and can develop serious life-threatening infections if not treated carefully.",
