    "longDesc": "Aromatic L-amino acid decarboxylase deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Aromatic L-amino acid decarboxylase deficiency is a rare genetic condition where your body cannot properly process certain amino acids (building blocks of protein) that contain aromatic rings—specifically those needed to make important brain chemicals like dopamine and serotonin. Without enough of the enzyme that breaks down these amino acids, patients typically develop severe neurological symptoms in infancy or early childhood, including movement disorders, developmental delays, low muscle tone, and sometimes problems with temperature regulation and blood pressure control. This is an inherited disorder passed down from parents to children through genes.",
