    "shortDesc": "Other disorders of propionate metabolism",
    "longDesc": "Other disorders of propionate metabolism",
    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to rare metabolic disorders affecting how your body processes propionate, a fatty acid produced during digestion of certain proteins and fats. When propionate metabolism doesn't work properly, it can accumulate in the blood and tissues, potentially causing neurological problems, developmental delays, or organ damage depending on the specific type and severity of the disorder.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, pediatricians, and geneticists use this code when diagnosing inherited metabolic conditions in both children and adults. It appears less frequently on patient EOB statements since these are relatively uncommon conditions, but you would see it if you've had genetic testing or specialized metabolic evaluation.",
