    "rawCode": "E7119",
    "shortDesc": "Other disorders of branched-chain amino-acid metabolism",
    "longDesc": "Other disorders of branched-chain amino-acid metabolism",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes rare metabolic disorders that affect how your body breaks down and uses branched-chain amino acids (leucine, isoleucine, and valine)—essential building blocks from protein. When these amino acids aren't processed correctly, they can build up in the blood and cause neurological problems, developmental delays, poor feeding, or muscle weakness. These conditions are usually genetic and may be detected through newborn screening, though symptoms can appear at different ages depending on the specific disorder.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, geneticists, and pediatricians use this code when diagnosing and managing inherited amino acid metabolism disorders. It commonly appears on EOBs for patients undergoing genetic testing, metabolic workups, or specialty nutritional management, particularly in pediatric cases, though it may also be used for adults with late-onset or undiagnosed metabolic conditions.",
