    "rawCode": "E7143",
    "shortDesc": "Iatrogenic carnitine deficiency",
    "longDesc": "Iatrogenic carnitine deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Iatrogenic carnitine deficiency means your body doesn't have enough carnitine (a substance that helps cells produce energy) because of a medical treatment or medication you received. This type of deficiency is caused by doctors or medications rather than a disease process—for example, certain dialysis treatments or medications can lower carnitine levels, leading to muscle weakness, fatigue, or heart problems if left untreated.",
    "whoUses": "Nephrologists (kidney specialists) and cardiologists commonly use this code, particularly in patients undergoing hemodialysis or taking certain medications that deplete carnitine. It may appear on EOBs for patients receiving dialysis, those with heart failure being treated with specific drugs, or those on long-term anticonvulsant therapy.",
