    "shortDesc": "Ruvalcaba-Myhre-Smith syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Ruvalcaba-Myhre-Smith syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Ruvalcaba-Myhre-Smith syndrome is a rare inherited genetic disorder that affects how your body processes certain amino acids and fatty acids, leading to developmental delays, intellectual disability, and distinctive physical features such as macrocephaly (enlarged head), facial abnormalities, and skin pigmentation changes. This condition is present from birth and is caused by mutations in specific genes that your parents passed down to you, though it's quite uncommon and may take time to diagnose since doctors must rule out other similar genetic disorders.",
    "whoUses": "Geneticists and genetic counselors primarily use this code for diagnosis and family counseling, along with pediatricians and developmental pediatricians who manage affected children. This code appears on EOB statements when genetic testing, genetic consultations, or specialized management of this rare genetic syndrome is billed, though it's an uncommon diagnosis that most patients will only see once or twice in their medical records.",
