    "shortDesc": "Other secondary carnitine deficiency",
    "longDesc": "Other secondary carnitine deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Your body uses a substance called carnitine to convert fats into energy for your cells to function properly. This code means you have developed a carnitine deficiency—meaning your carnitine levels are too low—as a result of another medical condition or factor, rather than from a genetic problem you were born with. Low carnitine can cause muscle weakness, fatigue, and problems with heart function, and treating the underlying cause (such as kidney disease, certain medications, or nutritional issues) is important to restore your carnitine levels.",
    "whoUses": "Nephrologists (kidney specialists), cardiologists, and metabolic disease specialists use this code, particularly when carnitine deficiency develops secondary to chronic kidney disease, dialysis, or other systemic conditions. This code appears moderately often on EOBs when patients require carnitine level testing, supplementation, or monitoring as part of treatment for an underlying medical condition.",
