    "longDesc": "Peroxisomal disorder, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "A peroxisomal disorder is a rare inherited metabolic condition affecting how your body breaks down certain fatty acids and other substances in specialized cell structures called peroxisomes. When these structures don't work properly, harmful substances can build up in your body, potentially affecting your nervous system, vision, and other organs. This code is used when doctors know you have a peroxisomal disorder but haven't identified which specific type it is.",
