    "shortDesc": "Zellweger syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Zellweger syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Zellweger syndrome is a rare, inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot properly break down fatty acids and certain other compounds because of problems with specialized structures in cells called peroxisomes. This leads to severe developmental problems, low muscle tone, intellectual disability, and often causes affected children to pass away in infancy or early childhood. The condition is present from birth and affects multiple organ systems, including the brain, liver, and kidneys.",
