    "plainEnglish": "Neonatal adrenoleukodystrophy is a severe genetic disorder that appears in newborns and infants, affecting how the body processes certain fatty acids in the brain and adrenal glands. This condition causes progressive damage to the protective coating around nerve cells (white matter), leading to serious neurological problems, developmental regression, seizures, and adrenal gland failure. If untreated, it can cause severe disability or death, which is why early detection through newborn screening is critical.",
