    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a rare inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot properly form peroxisomes—tiny structures inside cells that break down fatty acids and help manage harmful chemicals. When peroxisomes don't develop correctly, cells struggle to process certain fats and toxins, which can lead to severe neurological problems, liver damage, vision loss, and developmental delays. These are serious genetic conditions that typically appear early in childhood.",
