    "shortDesc": "Childhood cerebral X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy",
    "longDesc": "Childhood cerebral X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy",
    "plainEnglish": "Childhood cerebral X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy is a rare inherited disorder that damages the fatty coating (myelin) around nerve fibers in the brain and spinal cord, while also affecting how the adrenal glands function. This condition is caused by a genetic mutation on the X chromosome and typically appears in young boys, leading to progressive problems with movement, behavior, vision, hearing, and cognitive abilities. Without treatment, it can cause severe disability and life-threatening complications, though early diagnosis and certain therapies may help slow progression.",
