    "longDesc": "Adolescent X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy",
    "plainEnglish": "Adolescent X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy is a rare genetic disorder that affects the nervous system and adrenal glands, typically starting in the teenage years. In this condition, the body cannot properly break down certain fatty acids, which accumulate and damage the protective coating around nerve fibers in the brain and spinal cord, as well as affecting the adrenal glands that produce hormones. Patients may experience progressive problems with balance, coordination, vision, hearing, and muscle weakness, along with hormone deficiencies that affect growth and development.",
