    "code": "E71.528",
    "rawCode": "E71528",
    "shortDesc": "Other X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy",
    "longDesc": "Other X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy",
    "plainEnglish": "X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy is a rare inherited genetic disorder that affects how your body breaks down certain fatty acids, causing them to build up to toxic levels in the brain and nervous system. This damage progressively destroys the myelin (the protective coating around nerve fibers) and can impair the adrenal glands, leading to symptoms like vision problems, hearing loss, difficulty with coordination and movement, cognitive decline, and hormonal imbalances. This condition is inherited in an X-linked pattern, meaning it's passed down through genes on the X chromosome, and primarily affects males, though females can also be carriers or symptomatic.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, geneticists, and metabolic disease specialists use this code to diagnose and manage patients with this rare inherited neurometabolic disorder. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing genetic testing, specialized neuroimaging (MRI), or treatment with medications like Lorenzo's oil or other therapies aimed at slowing disease progression.",
