    "rawCode": "E71541",
    "shortDesc": "Zellweger-like syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Zellweger-like syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Zellweger-like syndrome is a rare genetic disorder that affects how your body breaks down certain fatty acids called very long-chain fatty acids, similar to a more severe condition called Zellweger syndrome. This causes fatty substances to build up in organs like the liver, brain, and kidneys, leading to developmental delays, weak muscle tone, vision problems, and other serious health issues that typically appear in infancy. The condition is inherited and present from birth, though it may not be immediately obvious until symptoms emerge in the first few weeks or months of life.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, pediatricians, and geneticists use this code when diagnosing and managing this rare inherited metabolic disorder. It occasionally appears on EOBs for patients receiving specialized genetic testing, imaging studies, or ongoing management at metabolic disorder centers, though it is uncommon in general medical practice.",
