    "plainEnglish": "This code describes rare inherited metabolic disorders where your body cannot properly break down certain fatty acids and other compounds because of defective structures called peroxisomes inside your cells. These disorders can affect brain development, vision, hearing, and bone growth, though symptoms vary widely depending on which specific peroxisomal function is impaired. If you have this diagnosis, it means genetic testing identified a peroxisomal disorder that doesn't fit into the more common categories, and your doctor is tracking this serious condition that may require ongoing specialist care.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic geneticists, pediatric neurologists, and genetic counselors use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with rare peroxisomal disorders. It appears less frequently on patient EOBs because these are uncommon genetic conditions, but when it does appear, it typically indicates referral to a specialty metabolic or genetic clinic for comprehensive management.",
