    "code": "E72.01",
    "rawCode": "E7201",
    "shortDesc": "Cystinuria",
    "longDesc": "Cystinuria",
    "plainEnglish": "Cystinuria is a rare inherited disorder where your body cannot properly reabsorb an amino acid called cystine, causing it to build up in your urine and form painful kidney stones. This condition is present from birth due to a genetic mutation, and people with cystinuria often experience kidney and bladder stones repeatedly throughout their lives unless they manage the condition with high fluid intake, dietary changes, and sometimes medications.",
    "whoUses": "Nephrologists (kidney specialists), urologists, and metabolic disease specialists use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with recurrent cystine stones or abnormal amino acid levels. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with chronic kidney stone disease, as the genetic nature of cystinuria requires ongoing monitoring and preventive care.",
