    "code": "E72.03",
    "rawCode": "E7203",
    "shortDesc": "Lowe's syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Lowe's syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Lowe's syndrome is a rare inherited genetic disorder that primarily affects males and causes problems with the eyes, kidneys, and muscles. People with this condition typically develop cataracts (clouding of the lens) early in life, struggle with kidney function that can lead to kidney disease, and experience muscle weakness and developmental delays. The condition is caused by a defect in a gene on the X chromosome, which is why it almost exclusively affects males who inherit the faulty gene from their mothers.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, ophthalmologists, nephrologists, and genetic specialists use this code when diagnosing and managing Lowe's syndrome in affected patients. This code may appear on EOB statements for patients receiving specialized care for complications related to the syndrome, such as cataract surgery or kidney function monitoring, though it is relatively uncommon given the rarity of the condition.",
