    "longDesc": "Argininemia",
    "plainEnglish": "Argininemia is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down an amino acid called arginine, causing it to build up to harmful levels in your blood and tissues. This buildup can damage the nervous system and liver, leading to developmental delays, seizures, muscle weakness, and progressive neurological problems if not managed early with a special diet and medication.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic geneticists, pediatricians, and genetic counselors use this code when diagnosing or managing patients with this condition, typically discovered through newborn screening or when a child shows unexplained developmental delays. It commonly appears on EOBs for specialty consultations, genetic testing, and management of this lifelong condition.",
