    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis refers to rare metabolic disorders affecting how your body processes lysine and hydroxylysine, which are amino acids (building blocks of protein) normally found in foods like meat, fish, and beans. When your body cannot break down these amino acids properly due to enzyme deficiencies, they can accumulate to harmful levels in your blood and urine, potentially causing symptoms like developmental delays, muscle weakness, seizures, or connective tissue problems. These are inherited genetic conditions that typically appear in childhood when symptoms first emerge.",
