    "shortDesc": "Disorders of ornithine metabolism",
    "longDesc": "Disorders of ornithine metabolism",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis refers to a metabolic disorder affecting how your body processes ornithine, an amino acid that plays a crucial role in the urea cycle—the process that removes nitrogen waste from your body. When ornithine metabolism is disrupted, nitrogen can build up to toxic levels in the blood and tissues, which can cause neurological problems, muscle weakness, vision loss, and developmental delays. The underlying cause is usually a genetic defect that affects the enzymes needed to properly handle ornithine.",
