    "plainEnglish": "A disorder of glycine metabolism means your body has trouble processing glycine, an amino acid (a building block of protein) that your cells normally use for important functions like making collagen and regulating your nervous system. When glycine metabolism is disrupted, it can build up in your blood or tissues or be in short supply, leading to various health problems depending on the specific type and severity—though the exact cause hasn't been pinpointed in your case. Symptoms can range from developmental delays and neurological issues to muscle weakness, depending on how significantly the disorder affects your body.",
