    "plainEnglish": "Trimethylaminuria is a rare metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down trimethylamine, a naturally occurring compound found in foods like eggs, liver, and beans. This causes trimethylamine to build up in your body and be released through sweat, urine, and breath, creating a strong, unpleasant \"fishy\" smell that can be socially distressing. The condition is usually inherited and lifelong, though symptoms can sometimes be managed through diet and medication.",
