    "shortDesc": "Primary hyperoxaluria, type 1",
    "longDesc": "Primary hyperoxaluria, type 1",
    "plainEnglish": "Primary hyperoxaluria type 1 is a rare genetic disorder where your body produces too much oxalate, a substance that normally gets filtered through your kidneys and into urine. When oxalate levels get too high, it can crystallize and form kidney stones, damage your kidneys over time, and in severe cases, cause calcium oxalate deposits in other parts of your body. This condition is inherited from your parents and starts from birth, though symptoms may not appear until later in life.",
