    "shortDesc": "Other secondary hyperoxaluria",
    "longDesc": "Other secondary hyperoxaluria",
    "plainEnglish": "Your body has higher-than-normal levels of oxalate (a chemical compound) in your urine, and this occurred as a result of another medical condition or illness rather than being an inherited genetic problem. Oxalate buildup can lead to kidney stones, kidney damage, or deposits in other tissues, and the underlying cause might be related to kidney disease, digestive problems, or certain medications or supplements you're taking.",
    "whoUses": "Nephrologists (kidney specialists), urologists, and internal medicine doctors use this code when managing patients with kidney disease or metabolic disorders that secondarily cause high urinary oxalate levels. It commonly appears on patient EOB statements when workup for recurrent kidney stones or abnormal urine chemistry has been performed.",
