    "code": "E72.59",
    "rawCode": "E7259",
    "shortDesc": "Other disorders of glycine metabolism",
    "longDesc": "Other disorders of glycine metabolism",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes an uncommon metabolic condition affecting how your body breaks down and uses glycine, an amino acid (building block of proteins). When glycine metabolism doesn't work properly, it can accumulate in your blood and other body tissues, potentially causing neurological symptoms, muscle weakness, or other complications depending on the specific type of disorder. While some glycine metabolism disorders are present from birth (inherited), this code captures various forms that don't fit into the more common specific diagnoses.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, geneticists, neurologists, and pediatricians use this code when diagnosing rare genetic or acquired glycine metabolism disorders. It appears on EOB statements less frequently than common diagnoses, typically only when a patient has been evaluated for unexplained developmental delays, seizures, or muscle problems and a metabolic workup has identified a glycine metabolism abnormality.",
