    "longDesc": "Disorders of gamma aminobutyric acid metabolism",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a problem with how your body processes GABA (gamma-aminobutyric acid), a chemical messenger in your brain that helps calm nerve activity and reduce anxiety. When GABA metabolism doesn't work properly, it can lead to neurological symptoms such as seizures, developmental delays, or movement disorders, depending on which specific enzyme or pathway is affected. These are rare inherited disorders that usually appear in infancy or early childhood.",
