    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a rare metabolic disorder affecting how your body processes amino acids—the building blocks of proteins. When amino acids aren't broken down properly, they can build up in your blood or urine to abnormal levels, potentially causing symptoms ranging from developmental delays and neurological problems to organ dysfunction, depending on which specific amino acid pathway is affected. You may have experienced symptoms like muscle weakness, intellectual disabilities, seizures, or unusual-smelling urine that prompted your doctor to investigate and identify this particular metabolic condition.",
