    "plainEnglish": "Lactose intolerance means your body has difficulty digesting lactose, a natural sugar found in milk and dairy products. When you consume dairy, you may experience bloating, gas, stomach cramping, or diarrhea because your small intestine doesn't produce enough of an enzyme called lactase that breaks down lactose. This code indicates you have been diagnosed with lactose intolerance, but the specific type (like primary, secondary, or congenital) hasn't been specified in your medical record.",
