    "code": "E74.00",
    "rawCode": "E7400",
    "shortDesc": "Glycogen storage disease, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Glycogen storage disease, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Glycogen storage disease is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down or store glycogen (a form of sugar your muscles and liver use for energy). This causes glycogen to build up abnormally in your cells, which can lead to muscle weakness, liver enlargement, low blood sugar, and other complications depending on which enzymes are affected. Without knowing the specific type of glycogen storage disease, this code indicates your doctor has diagnosed the condition but hasn't yet identified which of the ten known types you have.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, geneticists, metabolic disease specialists, and gastroenterologists typically diagnose and manage glycogen storage disease. This code commonly appears on EOB statements for patients with confirmed glycogen storage disease awaiting further genetic testing or specialist evaluation to determine the specific type.",
