    "rawCode": "E7402",
    "shortDesc": "Pompe disease",
    "longDesc": "Pompe disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Pompe disease is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot break down a sugar called glycogen, causing it to accumulate in muscles and organs over time. This buildup leads to progressive weakness in the muscles, particularly affecting the heart and the muscles needed for breathing, and the severity depends on when symptoms first appear—some people show signs in infancy while others develop problems later in childhood or adulthood.",
    "whoUses": "Geneticists, cardiologists, and neurologists primarily diagnose and manage Pompe disease, often with input from metabolic disease specialists. This code appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing genetic testing, enzyme replacement therapy (a specialized treatment), cardiac monitoring, or respiratory support related to this condition.",
