    "rawCode": "E7404",
    "shortDesc": "McArdle disease",
    "longDesc": "McArdle disease",
    "plainEnglish": "McArdle disease is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot break down a stored form of glucose called glycogen in your muscles. This happens because you lack an enzyme called muscle phosphorylase, which normally releases energy from glycogen during muscle activity. People with this condition experience muscle pain, weakness, fatigue during exercise, and sometimes dark urine after physical activity because muscles cannot access the energy they need to function properly.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, geneticists, and neurologists typically diagnose and manage McArdle disease, often after patients present with exercise intolerance and muscle symptoms. This code appears on EOB statements when a patient receives genetic testing, genetic counseling, or specialist evaluation for this rare glycogen storage disease.",
