    "longDesc": "Lysosome-associated membrane protein 2 [LAMP2] deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "LAMP2 deficiency is a rare genetic disorder where your body lacks a protein called LAMP2 that helps cells break down and recycle waste materials. Without this protein, harmful substances build up inside your cells, particularly affecting your heart muscle, skeletal muscles, and nervous system. This can cause serious problems like heart enlargement, muscle weakness, and difficulty swallowing or speaking.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, geneticists, neurologists, and metabolic disease specialists use this code when diagnosing or managing patients with this inherited lysosomal storage disorder. This code rarely appears on routine patient EOB statements but is important for specialized genetic disorder care and treatment planning.",
