    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to rare genetic disorders where your body has difficulty breaking down or storing glycogen (a form of stored sugar), but it's not one of the more common, specifically named types. These conditions can affect how your liver and muscles work, causing symptoms like low blood sugar episodes, muscle weakness, or an enlarged liver depending on which enzyme is affected. You may experience fatigue, growth delays, or liver problems.",
