    "shortDesc": "Essential fructosuria",
    "longDesc": "Essential fructosuria",
    "plainEnglish": "Essential fructosuria is a harmless genetic condition where your body cannot fully process a type of sugar called fructose, causing it to spill into your urine. This condition is benign and typically causes no symptoms or health problems—most people never realize they have it unless it's discovered through routine urine testing. Unlike other forms of fructose intolerance, essential fructosuria does not require dietary restrictions or cause illness.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians and metabolic specialists typically identify and manage this condition, usually after an accidental discovery on newborn screening or routine urinalysis. While it appears in medical records, essential fructosuria rarely shows up on patient EOB statements since it requires no treatment and typically incurs no billable clinical encounters beyond the initial diagnostic testing.",
