    "plainEnglish": "This code describes rare inherited disorders that affect how your body processes fructose, a natural sugar found in fruits, honey, and some sweetened foods. Unlike hereditary fructose intolerance (a more severe form), these other fructose metabolism disorders may cause various digestive issues, developmental delays, or metabolic complications depending on the specific type. When someone has one of these conditions, their body either cannot break down fructose properly or cannot use it efficiently for energy.",
