    "rawCode": "E744",
    "shortDesc": "Disorders of pyruvate metabolism and gluconeogenesis",
    "longDesc": "Disorders of pyruvate metabolism and gluconeogenesis",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes rare inherited metabolic disorders where your body cannot properly process pyruvate (a substance made during glucose breakdown) or create new glucose from non-carbohydrate sources (gluconeogenesis). These conditions disrupt how your body produces and uses energy, potentially causing low blood sugar, muscle weakness, developmental delays, or neurological symptoms depending on the specific type and severity.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic specialists, pediatricians, and genetic counselors use this code when diagnosing or managing inherited pyruvate metabolism disorders like pyruvate carboxylase deficiency or pyruvate dehydrogenase complex deficiency. It appears less frequently on patient EOBs but may show up in records for genetic testing, specialist consultations, or management of severe hypoglycemia.",
