    "shortDesc": "Other disorders of glucose transport",
    "longDesc": "Other disorders of glucose transport",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis refers to rare genetic or metabolic conditions that affect how your body transports glucose (sugar) into cells. These disorders prevent glucose from moving efficiently from the bloodstream into muscle, brain, and other tissues, even though blood sugar levels may be normal or high. Without proper glucose transport, cells cannot access the energy they need, which can cause fatigue, weakness, developmental delays, or other symptoms depending on which tissues are most affected.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic disease specialists, endocrinologists, geneticists, and neurologists use this code when evaluating patients with suspected glucose transporter defects (such as GLUT1 or GLUT3 deficiency). It is less commonly seen on patient EOB statements because these are rare conditions, but it may appear when patients undergo specialized genetic testing or are evaluated at tertiary care centers for unexplained metabolic or neurological symptoms.",
