    "rawCode": "E74819",
    "shortDesc": "Disorders of glucose transport, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Disorders of glucose transport, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a problem with how your body transports glucose (blood sugar) from one place to another, but the specific type of transport disorder hasn't been identified or documented in detail. Glucose transport disorders affect the proteins and mechanisms that move sugar into and out of cells, which can lead to abnormal blood sugar levels, organ dysfunction, or metabolic problems. Your doctor is noting that you have some form of glucose transport issue but needs more testing or specialist evaluation to pinpoint exactly which transport system is affected.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, metabolic specialists, and primary care physicians use this code when evaluating patients with suspected glucose transport defects (such as GLUT1 deficiency or other transporter disorders) that haven't yet been fully characterized. It commonly appears on EOBs as a temporary or working diagnosis while awaiting genetic testing, specialized metabolic workup, or more specific diagnostic confirmation.",
