    "longDesc": "SLC13A5 Citrate Transporter Disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "SLC13A5 Citrate Transporter Disorder is a rare genetic condition where your body cannot properly transport citrate (a natural compound involved in energy production and metabolism) in and out of cells. This happens because a specific protein called SLC13A5, which acts like a gatekeeper for citrate movement, is faulty or missing due to an inherited gene mutation. Patients with this condition typically experience seizures, developmental delays, and high levels of citrate in their blood and urine, especially beginning in infancy or early childhood.",
    "whoUses": "Metabolic geneticists and pediatric neurologists primarily use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with this rare inherited metabolic disorder. This code would rarely appear on a typical patient EOB, as it represents an uncommon genetic condition usually diagnosed through specialized genetic testing and metabolic screening in pediatric or genetics clinics.",
