    "plainEnglish": "Mucolipidosis IV is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot properly break down and recycle certain fatty substances and complex carbohydrates in cells, causing them to accumulate in various tissues. This buildup typically leads to progressive vision problems (often severe by childhood), developmental delays, muscle weakness, and in some cases, intellectual disability. The condition is present from birth and worsens over time, though the rate of progression can vary significantly between individuals.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, neurologists, geneticists, and ophthalmologists use this code when diagnosing and managing affected children. It appears on EOB statements when genetic testing, specialist evaluations, or imaging studies are performed for suspected metabolic disorders, though it is relatively uncommon in routine medical practice due to the rarity of the condition.",
