    "longDesc": "Other gangliosidosis",
    "plainEnglish": "Other gangliosidosis refers to a rare inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot properly break down certain fatty substances called gangliosides that accumulate in nerve and brain cells. This buildup can cause progressive neurological problems such as developmental delays, muscle weakness, loss of vision or hearing, seizures, and cognitive decline, though the severity and specific symptoms depend on which type of gangliosidosis is present and when symptoms begin. Patients with these conditions typically require ongoing neurological care and supportive treatment to manage symptoms as the disease progresses.",
