    "shortDesc": "Fabry (-Anderson) disease",
    "longDesc": "Fabry (-Anderson) disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Fabry disease is a rare inherited genetic condition where your body cannot properly break down certain fatty substances (called globotriaosylceramide), which then accumulate in your blood vessels, nerves, and organs over time. This buildup causes progressive damage that can lead to severe pain in the hands and feet, kidney disease, heart problems, and stroke. People with Fabry disease typically start experiencing symptoms in childhood or early adulthood and require lifelong management with specialized medications to slow the progression.",
    "whoUses": "Geneticists, cardiologists, nephrologists, and neurologists use this code when diagnosing and monitoring Fabry disease, as it affects multiple organ systems. This code appears on EOB statements for patients receiving genetic testing, enzyme replacement therapy (ERT), or ongoing specialist care for this rare lysosomal storage disorder.",
