    "shortDesc": "Krabbe disease",
    "longDesc": "Krabbe disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Krabbe disease is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where the body cannot properly break down a fatty substance called galactocerebroside, which builds up in the nervous system and damages the protective coating around nerve cells. This damage leads to progressive neurological symptoms that can include muscle weakness, loss of coordination, vision and hearing problems, developmental delays, and eventually severe disability. The disease typically appears in infancy or early childhood, though rare late-onset forms can occur in older individuals.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatricians, neurologists, genetic counselors, and metabolic disease specialists use this code when diagnosing and managing Krabbe disease. It appears on EOB statements primarily for children with symptoms prompting genetic testing and neurological workup, though given its rarity, most patients will never see this code on their insurance paperwork.",
