    "longDesc": "Niemann-Pick disease, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Niemann-Pick disease is a rare inherited condition where your body cannot properly break down certain fats (cholesterol and other lipids) inside cells. This causes these fats to build up in organs like the liver, spleen, brain, and bone marrow, leading to organ damage and serious health problems. The specific type or severity of your condition hasn't been further identified in your medical record.",
    "whoUses": "Geneticists, pediatricians, and metabolic disease specialists typically diagnose and manage Niemann-Pick disease. This code rarely appears on patient EOBs because the condition is very rare and usually diagnosed through specialized genetic testing in academic medical centers or pediatric specialty clinics.",
