    "shortDesc": "Metachromatic leukodystrophy",
    "longDesc": "Metachromatic leukodystrophy",
    "plainEnglish": "Metachromatic leukodystrophy is a rare inherited genetic disorder where the body cannot properly break down certain fatty substances in the brain and nervous system. These fats accumulate over time and damage the protective coating around nerve fibers, leading to progressive problems with movement, speech, vision, and thinking abilities. Symptoms typically appear in childhood and worsen over time, though the age of onset and severity can vary depending on the type.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, pediatricians, and genetic specialists use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with this inherited metabolic disorder. While it is a serious diagnosis, metachromatic leukodystrophy is rare enough that it may not commonly appear on routine patient EOB statements unless the patient is receiving specialized neurology or genetic counseling services.",
