    "longDesc": "Pelizaeus-Merzbacher disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Pelizaeus-Merzbacher disease is a rare genetic condition where the brain and nervous system don't develop myelin properly—myelin is the protective coating around nerve fibers that allows them to communicate effectively. This inherited disorder typically appears in infancy or early childhood and causes progressive problems with movement, coordination, muscle tone, and cognitive development. Patients may experience tremors, difficulty with balance and coordination, developmental delays, and gradual worsening of neurological function over time.",
    "whoUses": "Neurologists, pediatric neurologists, and geneticists primarily use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with this rare leukodystrophy. It appears on EOB statements less frequently than common diagnoses, but will be documented when a patient is evaluated for inherited neurological disorders or when ongoing specialty neurology care is provided.",
