    "plainEnglish": "Sphingolipidoses are rare genetic disorders where the body cannot properly break down certain fatty substances called sphingolipids that accumulate in cells throughout the body. This code refers to sphingolipidosis types that aren't more specifically identified—meaning your body is storing these fatty materials in organs like the brain, liver, spleen, or heart, which can cause progressive damage over time. Symptoms vary widely depending on which organs are affected and may include developmental delays, movement problems, vision or hearing loss, and organ enlargement.",
    "whoUses": "Geneticists, neurologists, and metabolic disease specialists use this code to diagnose and track rare inherited lipid storage disorders. It appears less frequently on patient EOB statements since these are uncommon conditions, but when present, it usually indicates specialized genetic testing, genetic counseling, or treatment at a metabolic disorder center.",
