    "rawCode": "E753",
    "shortDesc": "Sphingolipidosis, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Sphingolipidosis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Sphingolipidosis is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down certain fatty compounds called sphingolipids, which normally accumulate in cells. This buildup can damage nerve cells, organs, and tissues throughout the body, potentially causing developmental delays, movement problems, vision or hearing loss, and organ dysfunction depending on which sphingolipids are affected. The 'unspecified' designation means your doctor has diagnosed this condition but hasn't yet determined the specific type (like Gaucher disease or Niemann-Pick disease) or the exact genes involved.",
