    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a group of rare genetic disorders where your body has difficulty breaking down and storing certain fatty substances (lipids) in your cells, causing them to build up over time. These disorders can affect multiple organ systems including the brain, liver, and spleen, and symptoms vary widely depending on which specific lipid storage disorder is present—ranging from developmental delays and movement problems to organ enlargement and vision issues. The accumulation of these fats interferes with normal cell function because your body either lacks or has a deficiency in the enzymes needed to process these lipids correctly.",
