    "plainEnglish": "Hurler's syndrome is a rare inherited metabolic disorder in which your body cannot properly break down certain complex substances called glycosaminoglycans, causing them to accumulate in organs and tissues throughout your body. This buildup leads to progressive problems including developmental delays, joint stiffness, facial changes, heart issues, hearing loss, and vision problems, typically becoming noticeable in early childhood. The condition is inherited in an autosomal recessive pattern, meaning you need to inherit the faulty gene from both parents to develop it.",
