    "shortDesc": "Morquio A mucopolysaccharidoses",
    "longDesc": "Morquio A mucopolysaccharidoses",
    "plainEnglish": "Morquio A is a rare inherited metabolic disorder where your body cannot properly break down and recycle certain complex sugars called glycosaminoglycans, causing them to build up in your tissues and organs. This buildup leads to progressive bone and skeletal problems, including short stature, spine curvature, joint stiffness, and eventually affects organs like the heart and hearing. Children with this condition typically develop normal early, but symptoms appear during childhood as the sugar accumulation increases.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by pediatricians, metabolic disease specialists, genetic counselors, and orthopedic surgeons when managing patients with confirmed Morquio A syndrome. It appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing enzyme replacement therapy, genetic testing, monitoring visits, or orthopedic interventions related to skeletal complications of this lysosomal storage disorder.",
