    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis refers to a rare genetic condition where the body cannot properly modify certain proteins that are supposed to work in lysosomes—the 'recycling centers' of your cells that break down and dispose of waste materials. Without proper modification of these enzymes, they don't function correctly, which prevents cells from cleaning up waste products effectively. This typically leads to a buildup of toxic substances in cells and organs, causing progressive symptoms that may affect multiple body systems.",
