    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a rare genetic disorder where your body cannot properly break down glycoproteins—molecules made of proteins and sugars that are found throughout your body. When these molecules cannot be degraded correctly, they accumulate in your cells and tissues, which can cause progressive damage to organs like the liver, brain, and heart. Symptoms vary widely depending on which specific enzymes are affected, but may include developmental delays, seizures, liver problems, or heart issues that develop or worsen over time.",
