    "plainEnglish": "Lipoprotein deficiency means your body doesn't have enough of certain proteins that carry cholesterol and fats through your bloodstream. These lipoproteins are essential for transporting fats from food and your liver to cells throughout your body, and without adequate levels, your body struggles to process and deliver these nutrients properly. This can lead to nutritional deficiencies, digestive problems, and in some cases, nerve and vision issues if the condition is severe.",
