    "plainEnglish": "Barth syndrome is a rare inherited genetic disorder that primarily affects males and causes problems with how the body produces and uses energy in cells, particularly in the heart and muscles. People with this condition often experience heart muscle weakness (cardiomyopathy), low muscle tone, growth delays, and a tendency toward serious infections due to low white blood cell counts. The condition is caused by mutations in a gene that controls the production of a special fat called cardiolipin, which is essential for proper cell energy production.",
