    "shortDesc": "Other lipoprotein metabolism disorders",
    "longDesc": "Other lipoprotein metabolism disorders",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes an uncommon disorder affecting how your body processes lipoproteins—the particles that carry cholesterol and fats through your bloodstream. Unlike common high cholesterol, these rare lipid metabolism disorders involve specific problems with how lipoproteins are made, broken down, or used by your body, which can affect your heart health and other organs. If you see this code, it means your doctor identified a lipid problem that doesn't fit into the more common cholesterol categories.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, lipidologists, endocrinologists, and internal medicine doctors use this code when patients have unusual or complex fat metabolism issues that require specialized evaluation. It's less common on patient EOBs than codes for high cholesterol, but may appear when genetic lipid disorders or atypical cholesterol abnormalities are diagnosed during advanced testing.",
