    "plainEnglish": "This code means you have an abnormal level or type of cholesterol or fat in your blood, but your doctor hasn't identified the specific cause or named condition yet. Your body isn't processing fats and cholesterol the way it should, which could increase your risk of heart disease or stroke. This is often a temporary coding choice while your doctor is still running tests or evaluating which specific fat metabolism problem you have.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, and lipidologists use this code when a patient has abnormal lipid panel results but the specific disorder (like familial hypercholesterolemia or hypertriglyceridemia) hasn't been confirmed yet. It commonly appears on EOB statements as a diagnosis code alongside cholesterol or triglyceride testing.",
