    "plainEnglish": "Aicardi-Goutieres syndrome is a rare genetic disorder that affects the brain, immune system, and skin. This condition causes progressive brain damage, often starting in infancy, along with inflammation and a distinctive skin rash, usually on the face and buttocks. Affected individuals typically experience developmental delays, movement problems, and increased sensitivity to sunlight.",
    "whoUses": "This code is primarily used by pediatric neurologists, geneticists, and immunologists when diagnosing and managing this rare inherited condition. It appears less commonly on patient EOBs but would be documented when evaluating a child with unexplained early-onset neurological symptoms, brain calcifications, or when genetic testing confirms the diagnosis.",
