    "rawCode": "E8029",
    "shortDesc": "Other porphyria",
    "longDesc": "Other porphyria",
    "plainEnglish": "This code identifies a rare metabolic disorder affecting how your body breaks down and processes heme (a component of red blood cells). In these less common types of porphyria, your body produces abnormal amounts of porphyrins, which are chemical compounds that can build up in your tissues and cause symptoms ranging from severe abdominal pain and neurological problems to skin sensitivity and urine discoloration, depending on which specific type you have.",
    "whoUses": "Hematologists, gastroenterologists, neurologists, and geneticists use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with porphyria variants not classified as acute intermittent porphyria or cutaneous porphyria. This code appears less frequently on patient EOBs than more common diagnoses, typically following specialized testing or genetic evaluation for recurrent unexplained symptoms.",
