    "shortDesc": "Defects of catalase and peroxidase",
    "longDesc": "Defects of catalase and peroxidase",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes rare genetic disorders where your body lacks or has defective enzymes (catalase and peroxidase) needed to break down harmful hydrogen peroxide that forms during normal cell processes. Without these enzymes working properly, hydrogen peroxide builds up inside cells and can damage tissues, potentially affecting the skin, lungs, and other organs. The most common condition in this group is acatalasemia, where people have little to no catalase enzyme activity.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by hematologists, metabolic disease specialists, and geneticists when diagnosing and managing rare enzyme deficiency disorders. It rarely appears on patient EOB statements, as these are uncommon genetic conditions typically identified through specialized enzyme testing rather than routine care.",
