    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to rare problems with how your body processes bilirubin, a yellow substance created when red blood cells break down. When bilirubin metabolism doesn't work properly, it can accumulate in your blood and tissues, potentially causing yellowing of the skin and eyes (jaundice), dark urine, or other symptoms depending on the specific disorder. These conditions are less common than typical jaundice and may involve genetic factors or other underlying metabolic issues.",
