    "shortDesc": "Disorder of copper metabolism, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Disorder of copper metabolism, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a problem with how your body processes copper, an essential mineral needed for many bodily functions like bone formation, iron metabolism, and nerve function. When copper metabolism is disordered, your body either can't absorb enough copper, can't use it properly, or can't eliminate excess copper, leading to levels that are too high or too low. Symptoms vary depending on whether you have too little copper (weakness, nerve problems) or too much copper (liver damage, neurological issues), but this code is used when the specific type of copper disorder hasn't been clearly identified.",
