    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates your body has difficulty properly managing iron levels, but the specific type of iron problem hasn't been identified yet. Iron is essential for making healthy red blood cells and carrying oxygen through your body, so when iron metabolism goes wrong, you might experience fatigue, weakness, or other symptoms depending on whether you have too much or too little iron. Your doctor will likely need to run additional blood tests to pinpoint exactly what's happening with your iron levels and determine the underlying cause.",
