    "longDesc": "Hemochromatosis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Hemochromatosis is a condition where your body absorbs and stores too much iron from the food you eat. Over time, excess iron builds up in organs like the liver, heart, and pancreas, potentially causing damage and serious health problems. Your doctor has identified that you have hemochromatosis but hasn't yet determined the specific type or underlying cause.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by primary care physicians, gastroenterologists, hepatologists, and hematologists when evaluating patients with iron overload symptoms or abnormal iron lab results. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing diagnostic testing (iron panels, ferritin levels, genetic testing) or receiving treatment like phlebotomy (blood removal) or chelation therapy to reduce iron levels.",
