    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a group of disorders where your body doesn't properly regulate iron levels—either storing too much or too little—beyond the common conditions like hemochromatosis or simple iron deficiency. These metabolic problems can affect how your organs function and may require blood tests and dietary management or medication to bring iron levels back into balance.",
    "whoUses": "Hematologists, internists, and gastroenterologists use this code when evaluating patients with abnormal iron metabolism that doesn't fit typical iron overload or deficiency diagnoses. It's less commonly seen on patient EOB statements than more specific iron diagnoses, as it's typically used when the exact nature of the iron disorder is still being determined or is unusual.",
