    "plainEnglish": "This code describes problems with how your body processes and uses zinc, an essential mineral needed for immune function, wound healing, and protein synthesis. When you have a zinc metabolism disorder, your body may not be absorbing enough zinc from food, storing it properly, or using it effectively—which can lead to symptoms like hair loss, skin problems, delayed wound healing, weakened immunity, or loss of appetite.",
