    "plainEnglish": "Your body uses phosphorus (along with calcium) to build and maintain strong bones and teeth, and to control muscle and nerve function. This code means your doctor has identified a problem with how your body is handling phosphorus—it could be too much, too little, or an imbalance—but the specific type of phosphorus disorder hasn't been pinpointed yet. You might experience symptoms like bone pain, muscle weakness, or numbness, depending on whether your phosphorus levels are abnormal.",
