    "plainEnglish": "This code describes various uncommon problems with how your body controls calcium levels in the blood and bones. Calcium is essential for strong bones, nerve function, and muscle contractions, and your body carefully regulates how much calcium stays in your bloodstream versus how much gets stored in bones or excreted. When calcium metabolism goes wrong in ways that don't fit the more common diagnoses (like osteoporosis or high/low blood calcium), doctors use this code to document the condition.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, nephrologists (kidney specialists), and primary care physicians use this code when patients have calcium metabolism problems that don't fit standard diagnoses. It appears moderately often on EOBs for patients undergoing metabolic testing or being evaluated for bone health, kidney disease, or parathyroid disorders.",
    "billable": true,
