    "rawCode": "E83821",
    "shortDesc": "ENPP1 deficiency causing gen arterial calcifcn of infancy",
    "longDesc": "ENPP1 deficiency causing generalized arterial calcification of infancy",
    "plainEnglish": "This is a rare genetic disorder where the body lacks sufficient amounts of an enzyme called ENPP1, which normally prevents calcium from building up in arteries and soft tissues. Without enough of this enzyme, calcium deposits accumulate throughout the arterial system starting in infancy, which can severely restrict blood flow and cause serious heart and vascular complications. Babies with this condition may have symptoms like poor feeding, failure to thrive, and signs of heart stress.",
    "whoUses": "This code is primarily used by cardiologists, pediatric cardiologists, and geneticists who diagnose and manage this rare inherited metabolic disorder in infants. It appears infrequently on patient EOBs but is important for tracking specialized care, genetic testing, and cardiology interventions needed in affected children.",
