    "rawCode": "E83822",
    "shortDesc": "ENPP1 def cause autosom recess hypophosphate rickets type 2",
    "longDesc": "ENPP1 deficiency causing autosomal recessive hypophosphatemic rickets type 2",
    "plainEnglish": "This is a rare inherited bone disease caused by a deficiency of an enzyme called ENPP1. Without enough of this enzyme, your body cannot properly regulate phosphate levels, leading to soft, weak bones that don't harden correctly—a condition called rickets. Patients typically develop symptoms in childhood, including bone pain, delayed growth, and skeletal deformities, and the condition is inherited only when both parents carry the faulty gene.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatric endocrinologists, geneticists, and orthopedic specialists use this code when diagnosing and managing patients with this rare genetic disorder. It appears in medical records and specialist referrals rather than commonly on routine EOBs, as it affects a small population and typically requires specialized genetic testing and genetic counseling.",
