    "longDesc": "ABCC6 deficiency causing generalized arterial calcification of infancy",
    "plainEnglish": "This is a rare genetic condition where a person lacks or has defective ABCC6 protein, which normally prevents calcium from building up in arteries. Without this protein working properly, calcium deposits accumulate throughout the body's blood vessels very early in life, sometimes starting in infancy. This can severely restrict blood flow and put dangerous strain on the heart and other organs.",
    "whoUses": "Pediatric cardiologists, geneticists, and neonatal specialists use this code when diagnosing infants or young children with this inherited disorder. It rarely appears on routine patient EOB statements because it is an extremely rare condition, typically identified through specialized genetic testing and imaging in hospital or specialty clinic settings.",
