    "whoUses": "Nephrologists (kidney specialists), endocrinologists, and internal medicine doctors use this code when a patient has mineral metabolism issues that don't fit into more specific categories. It's less common on patient EOBs than codes for specific conditions like hypercalcemia or hypokalemia, but appears when laboratory work and clinical findings suggest a mineral disorder requiring ongoing management.",
