    "plainEnglish": "Cystic fibrosis is an inherited genetic disorder that damages the lungs and digestive system by causing thick, sticky mucus to build up in the airways, making it hard to breathe and increasing the risk of serious lung infections. When this condition primarily affects the lungs (pulmonary manifestations), patients typically experience chronic coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath, and recurrent respiratory infections that require ongoing treatment and monitoring.",
