    "whoUses": "Emergency medicine doctors, intensivists, nephrologists, and endocrinologists commonly diagnose and treat acute metabolic acidosis in hospital and emergency settings. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients admitted to the hospital or treated in the emergency department for acute illness, as it often accompanies serious conditions like sepsis, kidney failure, or diabetic crises.",
