    "rawCode": "E8802",
    "shortDesc": "Plasminogen deficiency",
    "longDesc": "Plasminogen deficiency",
    "plainEnglish": "Plasminogen deficiency means your body doesn't have enough plasminogen, a protein that helps break down blood clots. Without adequate plasminogen, your blood isn't able to dissolve clots efficiently, which can lead to abnormal clot formation in blood vessels and potentially cause serious complications like stroke or organ damage. This is a rare inherited bleeding disorder that usually requires specialized treatment to manage clotting risk.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by hematologists, coagulation specialists, and internal medicine physicians when diagnosing and managing patients with this rare inherited coagulation disorder. It appears on EOB statements when patients undergo specialized clotting studies or receive treatment for clot-related complications.",
