    "longDesc": "Other disorders of plasma-protein metabolism, not elsewhere classified",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes unusual problems with how your body processes proteins in your blood that aren't caused by a specific named disorder. Your liver and other organs produce various proteins that float in your bloodstream to carry nutrients, fight infections, and regulate fluid balance, but something is preventing these proteins from being made or functioning normally. You might notice symptoms like fluid buildup in your legs or abdomen, weakness, or infections, depending on which proteins are affected.",
