    "plainEnglish": "Generalized lipodystrophy is a rare condition where your body loses the ability to develop or maintain normal fat tissue throughout most of your body. This causes an abnormal loss of fat under the skin and around organs, which can lead to a very lean appearance, metabolic problems like insulin resistance and diabetes, and fatty buildup in the liver and muscles. People with this condition often struggle with managing blood sugar and cholesterol levels, and may experience complications affecting their heart, joints, and other organs.",
    "whoUses": "This code is primarily used by endocrinologists, geneticists, and internal medicine specialists who diagnose and manage metabolic disorders. It may appear on EOB statements for patients undergoing evaluation for severe metabolic dysfunction, genetic testing, or treatment of diabetes and lipid abnormalities related to this underlying lipodystrophy.",
