    "plainEnglish": "Tumor lysis syndrome is a serious condition that occurs when cancer cells die rapidly—usually after chemotherapy or radiation treatment—and release their contents into the bloodstream. This sudden release of potassium, phosphate, and other chemicals can cause dangerous imbalances in your blood that affect your heart rhythm, kidneys, and nervous system, potentially leading to seizures or organ failure if not treated quickly.",
