    "code": "E88.810",
    "rawCode": "E88810",
    "shortDesc": "Metabolic syndrome",
    "longDesc": "Metabolic syndrome",
    "plainEnglish": "Metabolic syndrome is a cluster of health conditions that occur together, increasing your risk for heart disease and diabetes. These conditions typically include high blood pressure, high blood sugar, excess belly fat, and abnormal cholesterol or triglyceride levels—and having multiple of these at the same time creates a greater overall health risk than having just one condition alone.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, cardiologists, endocrinologists, and internal medicine doctors commonly diagnose and manage metabolic syndrome. This code frequently appears on patient EOB statements as it's a common diagnosis used to track patients who need preventive care and lifestyle modifications.",
