    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a condition where your body's cells don't respond properly to insulin, the hormone that helps regulate blood sugar levels. This insulin resistance can occur for reasons other than the common metabolic syndrome or prediabetes, and it may contribute to difficulty controlling blood sugar, weight gain, or other metabolic problems even if you don't have traditional diabetes.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by endocrinologists, internal medicine physicians, and primary care doctors when documenting insulin resistance that doesn't fit into more specific categories. It appears on EOB statements when a patient has been evaluated for metabolic or glucose-control issues, though it's less common than codes for prediabetes or metabolic syndrome.",
