    "code": "E88.82",
    "rawCode": "E8882",
    "shortDesc": "Obesity due to disruption of MC4R pathway",
    "longDesc": "Obesity due to disruption of MC4R pathway",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a rare genetic form of obesity caused by a mutation in a gene called MC4R (melanocortin-4 receptor), which normally helps control appetite and body weight. People with this condition have a faulty signal that regulates hunger and fullness, causing them to feel constantly hungry and gain weight even when eating normal amounts of food. Unlike typical obesity, this is not caused by overeating due to lack of willpower but rather by a specific genetic defect affecting the brain's appetite control system.",
    "whoUses": "Endocrinologists, pediatric metabolic specialists, and geneticists primarily diagnose and manage this condition through genetic testing and specialized treatment programs. This code appears on EOB statements when patients undergo genetic evaluation for severe early-onset obesity, particularly in children, and is less common on routine insurance claims.",
