    "code": "E88.A",
    "rawCode": "E88A",
    "shortDesc": "Wasting disease (syndrome) due to underlying condition",
    "longDesc": "Wasting disease (syndrome) due to underlying condition",
    "plainEnglish": "Wasting disease means your body is losing muscle mass and weight because of another underlying medical condition—it's not intentional weight loss from dieting or lifestyle changes. This occurs when a serious chronic illness (like cancer, tuberculosis, HIV/AIDS, or severe kidney disease) causes your body to break down muscle tissue faster than it can rebuild it, leading to weakness and progressive loss of body mass. Patients with wasting typically feel fatigued, become visibly thinner, and experience muscle weakness that interferes with daily activities.",
    "whoUses": "Oncologists, infectious disease specialists, nephrologists, and internal medicine physicians use this code when documenting muscle wasting secondary to cancer, chronic infections, or organ failure. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing cancer treatment, managing advanced HIV, or dealing with end-stage renal disease, and helps justify nutritional support or physical therapy interventions.",
